INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('67ePnWfvKYVd','en','''Hung Hop Camphor Trunk Factory''',0,replace('A visit to Tai Kok Tsui uncovered a treasure chest of fantastic sights: a giant ship’s anchor wrapped like a present, a worker cranking open spent fire extinguishers for recycling, and many Ghost Signs from Hong Kong’s industrial past.\n\nThis one was a mystery: “洪合樟木槓廠” (hung4 hap6 zoeng1 muk6 gong3 cong2). “樟木” (camphor wood) and “廠” (factory) were clear but “槓”? “槓” can mean a few things including “horizontal bar” and “carrying pole” - we couldn’t imagine a time when demand for carrying poles would call for such a huge factory!\n\nMore digging revealed that this was the Hung Hop Wooden Trunk Factory, which used to make beautifully carved chests from Camphor.\n\nCamphor goods used to be produced widely in Hong Kong. The tree is a native species. The oldest tree in Hong Kong is a 400 year old Camphor in She Shan Village, the 社山神木 (se5 saan1 san4 muk6 She Shan Big Tree).\n\nCamphor wood is known for its fragrance and as a natural repellent against moths and boring insects. Chests made of Camphor were commonly gifted to women when they got married. Camphor chests kept blankets, linens, clothes and personal papers fresh. They were often used in Chinese households. Wealthy homes had ornate camphor chests intricately carved with dragons, ships, people, patterns and animal motifs. In the 18th and 19th centuries, camphor chests were used to transport tea, porcelain, and silks from China to Europe.\n\nThere isn’t much information available on the Hung Hop Factory. Some sources say it was established in the 1950s and closed with the decline in Hong Kong manufacturing. But their beautiful trunks are still around on the second hand market, and so are the Ghost Signs on their old factory building.','\n',char(10)),0,'113 Tung Chau St, Tai Kok Tsui',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"113","streetName":"Tung Chau Street","neighbourhood":"Tai Kok Tsui","district":"YTM","region":"KL","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('67ePnWfvKYVd','zh-hant','''Hung Hop Camphor Trunk Factory'' （洪跳樟樹林工廠）',1,replace('參觀大角咀之後，發現咗一個充滿奇異景象嘅寶庫：禮物噉包裹住巨輪嘅錨，一名工人打開用過嘅滅火器進行回收，以及好多來自香港工業歷史嘅幽靈標誌。\n\n這是一個謎：“洪合樟木槓廠”（hung4 hap6 zoeng1 muk6 gong3 cong2）。 “樟木”（樟木）和“廠”（工廠）係明確嘅，但“槓”呢？ “槓”可以表示一些東西，包括“單槓”和“搬運桿”——我們無法想象對搬運桿的需求會需要如此龐大的工廠！\n\n進一步挖掘後發現，係鴻躍木箱廠，以前用樟腦製作雕刻精美嘅箱。\n\n樟腦製品過去喺香港廣泛生產。 呢樖樹係本地物種。 香港最古老嘅樹係社山神木（ se5 saan1 san4 muk6社山大樹），係社山神木。\n\n樟木以其香味和對飛蛾和無聊昆蟲的天然驅蟲劑而聞名。 樟腦製成嘅箱通常係喺女性結婚時送畀佢哋嘅礼物。 樟腦箱令毛氈、床單、衫同個人文件保持新鮮。 它們經常被中國家庭使用。 富裕的家庭有華麗的樟腦箱，上面錯綜複雜地雕刻著龍、船、人、圖案和動物圖案。 18世紀同19世紀緊，樟腦箱被用嚟把茶葉、瓷器和絲綢由中國運到歐洲。\n\n關於Hung Hop Factory嘅信息唔多。 一些消息來源話，它成立於1950年代，隨著香港製造業嘅衰落而關閉。 但佢哋靚嘅行李箱仍然喺二手市場上，佢哋舊廠房上嘅Ghost Signs也是如此。','\n',char(10)),1,'通州街113號油尖旺區',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"113","streetName":"通州街","neighbourhood":"大角咀","district":"油尖旺區","region":"九龍","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('67ePnWfvKYVd','zh-hans','''Hung Hop Camphor Trunk Factory'' （洪跳樟树林工厂）',1,replace('参观大角咀后，发现了一个充满奇异景象的宝库：像礼物一样包裹着巨轮的锚，一名工人打开用过的灭火器进行回收，以及许多来自香港工业历史的幽灵标志。\n\n这是一个谜：“洪合樟木槓廠” （hung4 hap6 zoeng1 muk6 gong3 cong2）。“樟木”（樟木）和“廠”（工厂）是明确的，但“槓”呢？“槓”可以表示一些东西，包括“单杠”和“搬运杆”——我们无法想象对搬运杆的需求会需要如此庞大的工厂！\n\n进一步挖掘后发现，这是鸿跃木箱厂，以前用樟脑制作雕刻精美的箱子。\n\n樟脑制品过去在香港广泛生产。这棵树是本地物种。香港最古老的树是社山神木（se5 saan1 san4 muk6 社山大树），是社山神木。\n\n樟木以其香味和对飞蛾和无聊昆虫的天然驱虫剂而闻名。樟脑制成的箱子通常是在女性结婚时送给她们的礼物。樟脑箱让毯子、床单、衣服和个人文件保持新鲜。它们经常被中国家庭使用。富裕的家庭有华丽的樟脑箱，上面错综复杂地雕刻着龙、船、人、图案和动物图案。在 18 世纪和 19 世纪，樟脑箱被用来将茶叶、瓷器和丝绸从中国运到欧洲。\n\n关于 Hung Hop Factory 的信息不多。一些消息来源说，它成立于 1950 年代，随着香港制造业的衰落而关闭。但他们漂亮的行李箱仍然在二手市场上，他们旧厂房上的 Ghost Signs 也是如此。','\n',char(10)),1,'通州街113号油尖旺区',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"113","streetName":"通州街","neighbourhood":"大角咀","district":"油尖旺区","region":"九龙","country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('K22bqphvXIDg','en','''Tin Yin Medicine Firm''',0,'Seemingly invisible to passers-by unattuned to these relics of the past, such phantom outlines of old signage are sometimes referred to as ‘revenants,’ left behind like an afterimage burned into the signboard, the retina, and the memory.',0,'92 Fuk Wing St, Sham Shui Po',1,'{"buildingName":"Sheung Fook Building","buildingNumberFrom":"92","streetName":"Fuk Wing Street","neighbourhood":"Sham Shui Po","district":"SSP","region":"KL","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('K22bqphvXIDg','zh-hant','溧天燕藥業 ㄏ',1,'對於唔熟悉呢啲過去遺蹟嘅路人來說，呢啲幻影輪廓似乎係睇唔見嘅，呢種舊標牌嘅幻影輪廓有時被稱為“亡魂”，就好似烙印喺招牌、視網膜和記憶中嘅殘影一樣留低。',1,'常福大廈福榮街92號深水埗區',1,'{"buildingName":"常福大廈","buildingNumberFrom":"92","streetName":"福榮街","neighbourhood":"深水埗","district":"深水埗區","region":"九龍","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('K22bqphvXIDg','zh-hans','“天燕药业”',1,'对于不熟悉这些过去遗迹的路人来说，这些幻影轮廓似乎是看不见的，这种旧标牌的幻影轮廓有时被称为“亡魂”，就像烙印在招牌、视网膜和记忆中的残影一样留下来。',1,'常福大厦福荣街92号深水埗區',1,'{"buildingName":"常福大厦","buildingNumberFrom":"92","streetName":"福荣街","neighbourhood":"深水埗","district":"深水埗區","region":"九龙","country":"香港特区"}');
