INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('TWL4eGFgY1ac','en','''Tsui King Lau'' & ''_Hang''',0,replace('We spotted this Ghost Sign on our way to check out Jim Jim Jim Studio in Yau Ma Tei.\n\nIt may have been part of the spectacular signage for 醉瓊樓飯店 (zeoi3 king4 lau4 faan6 dim3 Tsui King Lau Restaurant) at 7 Saigon Street in Jordan. Tsui King Lau specialises in Hakka food and you can still see the main sign on the front of the building.\n\nThe restaurant used to have a huge blue and orange neon sign that came down some time between 2011 and 2016 according to Google Streetview. Saigon street used to have lots of great neon, including a big Nokia sign that’s proven less long lasting than those brick phones we all used to have.\n\nThere is a small silver lining though. A large billboard that blocked the side of this building came down along with all those neons and, as a result, this Ghost Sign has been revealed.\n\nYou win some, you lose some....','\n',char(10)),0,'9 Saigon St, Yau Ma Tei',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"9","streetName":"Saigon Street","neighbourhood":"Yau Ma Tei","district":"YTM","region":"KL","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('TWL4eGFgY1ac','zh-hant','''Tsui King Lau'' & ''_Hang''',1,replace('我哋喺去油馬地嘅吉姆吉姆吉姆工作室嘅路上發現咗呢個幽靈標誌。\n\n它可能係位於佐敦西貢街7號醉糍店（ zeoi3 king4 lau4 faan6 dim3翠景樓餐廳）壯觀嘅招牌嘅一部分。 Tsui King Lau專門提供客家菜，你仍然可以喺大樓正面睇到主要招牌。\n\n根據穀謌街景嘅數據，呢間餐廳曾經有一個巨大嘅藍色同橙色霓虹燈招牌，2011年至2016年間緊嘅某個時候拆除了。 西貢街曾經有好多好勁嘅霓虹燈，包括一個巨大嘅諾基亞標誌，事實證明它不如我哋過去擁有嘅嗰啲磚頭手機耐用。\n\n之，仲有一線希望。 擋住這座建築側面嘅大型廣告牌與所有呢啲霓虹燈一起倒下，結果，呢個幽靈標誌被揭露了。\n\n你贏了一些，你輸了一些......','\n',char(10)),1,'西貢街9號油尖旺區',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"9","streetName":"西貢街","neighbourhood":"油麻地","district":"油尖旺區","region":"九龍","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('TWL4eGFgY1ac','zh-hans','''Tsui King Lau'' & ''_Hang''',1,replace('我们在去油马地的吉姆吉姆吉姆工作室的路上发现了这个幽灵标志。\n\n它可能是位于佐敦西贡街 7 号醉瓊樓店（zeoi3 king4 lau4 faan6 dim3 翠景楼餐厅）壮观的招牌的一部分。Tsui King Lau 专门提供客家菜，您仍然可以在大楼正面看到主要招牌。\n\n根据谷歌街景的数据，这家餐厅曾经有一个巨大的蓝色和橙色霓虹灯招牌，在 2011 年至 2016 年间的某个时候拆除了。西贡街曾经有很多很棒的霓虹灯，包括一个巨大的诺基亚标志，事实证明它不如我们过去拥有的那些砖头手机耐用。\n\n不过，还有一线希望。挡住这座建筑侧面的大型广告牌与所有这些霓虹灯一起倒下，结果，这个幽灵标志被揭露了。\n\n你赢了一些，你输了一些......','\n',char(10)),1,'西贡街9号油尖旺区',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"9","streetName":"西贡街","neighbourhood":"油麻地","district":"油尖旺区","region":"九龙","country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('MPh1CG2u2ewu','en','''Jim Jim Photo Studio''',0,replace('Sammy Photo Studio is a beautiful old shop in a second floor walk-up in Yau Ma Tei and is one the few film photo studios left in Hong Kong. This institution is a must see for everyone - the shop’s kindly proprietor, Lam Kwok-shing takes portraits with his venerable Hasselblad 501C, develops photos in his dark room and retouches by hand. \n\nHurry down as this historical local business needs and deserves everyone’s support!\n\nMr. Lam once told @varsity.cuhk that “there are days when the customers do not come, days that are becoming more common with each passing year. ​​It is like waiting for a friend. They have promised that they would come back to take photos, but you don’t know when they will come. The waiting process is cruel.” \n\nWhen we learned that Sammy Photo Studio had once been known as 尖尖照相 (zim1 zim1 ziu3 soeng1 Jim Jim Studio) and that the old signage is still there, we rushed over. \n\nIt turned out this entire building, just opposite @eaton.hk , is a full on Ghost Sign gallery with old signs for a tailor shop 黃澤農洋服 (wong4 zaak6 nung4 joeng4 fuk6) and a fortune teller 利士林 (lei6 si6 lam4 / Li Si Lam). Li was a fortune teller of the 玄學 (jyun4 hok6 Neo-Daoism) tradition, a combination of Daoist and Confusion practices. The fortune teller’s signboard was done by the popular travel writer and journalist, 吳灞陵 (ng4 baa3 ling4 Ng Ba Ling), whose name can be seen to the left.\n\nGo check out these Ghost Signs while you can but whatever you do, don’t let Sammy Studio go the same way as the other old businesses in this building. Mr. Lam will be happy to see you!','\n',char(10)),0,'11 Pak Hoi St, Yau Ma Tei',1,'{"buildingName":"Chung Pak Mansion","buildingNumberFrom":"11","streetName":"Pak Hoi Street","neighbourhood":"Yau Ma Tei","district":"YTM","region":"KL","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('MPh1CG2u2ewu','zh-hant','''吉姆吉姆照相馆''',1,replace('Sammy Photo Studio係一家靚嘅老店，位於油馬地嘅二樓步行街，係香港僅存嘅幾家電影照相馆之一。 呢間店係個個都必去嘅地方-店主Lam Kwok-shing用佢嗰架古老嘅哈苏501C相機拍攝肖像，喺佢嘅暗房度沖洗照片，並手工修飾。 \n\n快啲，因為呢個歷史悠久嘅本地企業需要並且值得大家嘅撐！\n\n林先生曾對@varsity.cuhk表示：「有些日子顧客不來，而這些日子一年比一年常見。就好似等待朋友一樣。 佢哋已經答應會回來拍照，但你唔知佢哋幾時會嚟。 等待過程係殘酷嘅。 \n\n当我们得知Sammy Photo Studio曾經被稱為尖尖照相（ zim1 zim1 ziu3 soeng1 Jim Jim Studio ）並且舊標牌仍然存在時，我哋趕了過去。 \n\n原來這整棟建築，就在@eaton.hk 的對面，是一個完整的鬼招牌畫廊，上面有一家裁縫店黃洋服（wong4 zaak6 nung4 joeng4 fuk6）和算命師利士林（lei6 si6 lam4 / Li Si Lam）。 李是玄學（jyun4 hok6新道教）傳統的算命先生，這是道教和混亂實踐的結合。 相士嘅招牌係由受歡迎嘅旅行作家同記者雒陵（ ng4 baa3 ling4 Ng Ba Ling ）完成嘅，佢嘅名可以喺左邊睇到。\n\n趁你有機會嘅時候去睇吓呢啲Ghost Signs，但無論你做乜，都唔好畀Sammy Studio走棟樓度其他老企業一樣嘅路。 林先生會好开心見到您！','\n',char(10)),1,'CHUNG PAK MANSION北海街11號油尖旺區',1,'{"buildingName":"CHUNG PAK MANSION","buildingNumberFrom":"11","streetName":"北海街","neighbourhood":"油麻地","district":"油尖旺區","region":"九龍","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('MPh1CG2u2ewu','zh-hans','''吉姆吉姆照相馆''',1,replace('Sammy Photo Studio 是一家美丽的老店，位于油马地的二楼步行街，是香港仅存的几家电影照相馆之一。这家店是每个人都必去的地方 - 店主 Lam Kwok-shing 用他那辆古老的哈苏 501C 相机拍摄肖像，在他的暗房里冲洗照片，并手工修饰。\n\n快点，因为这个历史悠久的本地企业需要并且值得大家的支持！\n\n林先生曾对 @varsity.cuhk 表示：「有些日子顾客不来，而这些日子一年比一年常见。这就像等待朋友一样。他们已经答应会回来拍照，但你不知道他们什么时候会来。等待过程是残酷的。\n\n当我们得知 Sammy Photo Studio 曾经被称为尖尖照相 （zim1 zim1 ziu3 soeng1 Jim Jim Studio） 并且旧标牌仍然存在时，我们赶了过去。\n\n原来这整栋建筑，就在@eaton.hk 的对面，是一个完整的鬼招牌画廊，上面有一家裁缝店黃澤農洋服 （wong4 zaak6 nung4 joeng4 fuk6） 和算命师利士林 （lei6 si6 lam4 / Li Si Lam）。李是玄學（jyun4 hok6 新道教）传统的算命先生，这是道教和混乱实践的结合。算命先生的招牌是由受欢迎的旅行作家和记者吳灞陵 （ng4 baa3 ling4 Ng Ba Ling） 完成的，他的名字可以在左边看到。\n\n趁你有机会的时候去看看这些 Ghost Signs，但无论你做什么，都不要让 Sammy Studio 走这栋楼里其他老企业一样的路。林先生会很高兴见到您！','\n',char(10)),1,'CHUNG PAK MANSION北海街11号油尖旺区',1,'{"buildingName":"CHUNG PAK MANSION","buildingNumberFrom":"11","streetName":"北海街","neighbourhood":"油麻地","district":"油尖旺区","region":"九龙","country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('-7dU5oH9HEYk','en','''Wong Chak Lon Tailor''',0,replace('Sammy Photo Studio is a beautiful old shop in a second floor walk-up in Yau Ma Tei and is one the few film photo studios left in Hong Kong. This institution is a must see for everyone - the shop’s kindly proprietor, Lam Kwok-shing takes portraits with his venerable Hasselblad 501C, develops photos in his dark room and retouches by hand. \n\nHurry down as this historical local business needs and deserves everyone’s support!\n\nMr. Lam once told @varsity.cuhk that “there are days when the customers do not come, days that are becoming more common with each passing year. ​​It is like waiting for a friend. They have promised that they would come back to take photos, but you don’t know when they will come. The waiting process is cruel.” \n\nWhen we learned that Sammy Photo Studio had once been known as 尖尖照相 (zim1 zim1 ziu3 soeng1 Jim Jim Studio) and that the old signage is still there, we rushed over. \n\nIt turned out this entire building, just opposite @eaton.hk , is a full on Ghost Sign gallery with old signs for a tailor shop 黃澤農洋服 (wong4 zaak6 nung4 joeng4 fuk6) and a fortune teller 利士林 (lei6 si6 lam4 / Li Si Lam). Li was a fortune teller of the 玄學 (jyun4 hok6 Neo-Daoism) tradition, a combination of Daoist and Confusion practices. The fortune teller’s signboard was done by the popular travel writer and journalist, 吳灞陵 (ng4 baa3 ling4 Ng Ba Ling), whose name can be seen to the left.\n\nGo check out these Ghost Signs while you can but whatever you do, don’t let Sammy Studio go the same way as the other old businesses in this building. Mr. Lam will be happy to see you!','\n',char(10)),0,'11 Pak Hoi St, Yau Ma Tei',1,'{"buildingName":"Chung Pak Mansion","buildingNumberFrom":"11","streetName":"Pak Hoi Street","neighbourhood":"Yau Ma Tei","district":"YTM","region":"KL","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('-7dU5oH9HEYk','zh-hant','''黄泽伦裁縫店''',1,replace('Sammy Photo Studio係一家靚嘅老店，位於油馬地嘅二樓步行街，係香港僅存嘅幾家電影照相馆之一。 呢間店係個個都必去嘅地方-店主Lam Kwok-shing用佢嗰架古老嘅哈苏501C相機拍攝肖像，喺佢嘅暗房度沖洗照片，並手工修飾。 \n\n快啲，因為呢個歷史悠久嘅本地企業需要並且值得大家嘅撐！\n\n林先生曾對@varsity.cuhk表示：「有些日子顧客不來，而這些日子一年比一年常見。就好似等待朋友一樣。 佢哋已經答應會回來拍照，但你唔知佢哋幾時會嚟。 等待過程係殘酷嘅。 \n\n当我们得知Sammy Photo Studio曾經被稱為尖尖照相（ zim1 zim1 ziu3 soeng1 Jim Jim Studio ）並且舊標牌仍然存在時，我哋趕了過去。 \n\n原來這整棟建築，就在@eaton.hk 的對面，是一個完整的鬼招牌畫廊，上面有一家裁縫店黃洋服（wong4 zaak6 nung4 joeng4 fuk6）和算命師利士林（lei6 si6 lam4 / Li Si Lam）。 李是玄學（jyun4 hok6新道教）傳統的算命先生，這是道教和混亂實踐的結合。 相士嘅招牌係由受歡迎嘅旅行作家同記者雒陵（ ng4 baa3 ling4 Ng Ba Ling ）完成嘅，佢嘅名可以喺左邊睇到。\n\n趁你有機會嘅時候去睇吓呢啲Ghost Signs，但無論你做乜，都唔好畀Sammy Studio走棟樓度其他老企業一樣嘅路。 林先生會好开心見到您！','\n',char(10)),1,'CHUNG PAK MANSION北海街11號油尖旺區',1,'{"buildingName":"CHUNG PAK MANSION","buildingNumberFrom":"11","streetName":"北海街","neighbourhood":"油麻地","district":"油尖旺區","region":"九龍","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('-7dU5oH9HEYk','zh-hans','''黄泽伦裁缝店''',1,replace('Sammy Photo Studio 是一家美丽的老店，位于油马地的二楼步行街，是香港仅存的几家电影照相馆之一。这家店是每个人都必去的地方 - 店主 Lam Kwok-shing 用他那辆古老的哈苏 501C 相机拍摄肖像，在他的暗房里冲洗照片，并手工修饰。\n\n快点，因为这个历史悠久的本地企业需要并且值得大家的支持！\n\n林先生曾对 @varsity.cuhk 表示：「有些日子顾客不来，而这些日子一年比一年常见。这就像等待朋友一样。他们已经答应会回来拍照，但你不知道他们什么时候会来。等待过程是残酷的。\n\n当我们得知 Sammy Photo Studio 曾经被称为尖尖照相 （zim1 zim1 ziu3 soeng1 Jim Jim Studio） 并且旧标牌仍然存在时，我们赶了过去。\n\n原来这整栋建筑，就在@eaton.hk 的对面，是一个完整的鬼招牌画廊，上面有一家裁缝店黃澤農洋服 （wong4 zaak6 nung4 joeng4 fuk6） 和算命师利士林 （lei6 si6 lam4 / Li Si Lam）。李是玄學（jyun4 hok6 新道教）传统的算命先生，这是道教和混乱实践的结合。算命先生的招牌是由受欢迎的旅行作家和记者吳灞陵 （ng4 baa3 ling4 Ng Ba Ling） 完成的，他的名字可以在左边看到。\n\n趁你有机会的时候去看看这些 Ghost Signs，但无论你做什么，都不要让 Sammy Studio 走这栋楼里其他老企业一样的路。林先生会很高兴见到您！','\n',char(10)),1,'CHUNG PAK MANSION北海街11号油尖旺区',1,'{"buildingName":"CHUNG PAK MANSION","buildingNumberFrom":"11","streetName":"北海街","neighbourhood":"油麻地","district":"油尖旺区","region":"九龙","country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('emqJbsDvxCqX','en','''Yuet Hing Co.''',0,replace('A restaurant and a Prizemart closed down and when all their air conditioning units and lights came off the building this Ghost Sign was revealed.\n\n粵興公司 (Yuet Hing Company) used to deal in electronic scales, paper, printing products and printing services at this location at 15 Nanking Street. They still exist but they’ve moved over about seven blocks west, leaving behind this sign which was written by the calligrapher, 黄維瑁 (Huang Weichang or Wong Wai Cheong).\n\nProfessor Wong was born in 1901 or 1902 and was quite a big name in the Chinese calligraphy world. He died in 1993 but his works live on in the collections of the Hong Kong Museum of Art. They’ve appeared in at least three exhibitions there: “Hong Kong Calligraphy” (1990), “Modern Chinese Painting and Calligraphy from the Taiyilou Collection” (1991) and “Fragrance of Ink and Vermillion” (1999).\n\nThe Professor seems to have specialised in Clerical Script (隸書), which tends to be used in Hong Kong signage when somebody wants to give a feeling of gravitas or something of the old world. Businesses and institutions that might favour Clerical Script would be schools, stationery stores and, perhaps, printers.\n\nMaybe the proprietors of Yuet Hing Company thought Professor Wong’s balanced calligraphy would be perfect for advertising their scales?','\n',char(10)),0,'9 Jordan Rd, Yau Ma Tei',1,'{"buildingName":"Ko Kie Building","buildingNumberFrom":"9","buildingNumberTo":"11","streetName":"Jordan Road","neighbourhood":"Yau Ma Tei","district":"YTM","region":"KL","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('emqJbsDvxCqX','zh-hant','''悅興公司''',1,replace('一家餐廳同一家Prizemart關門了，当佢哋所有嘅冷氣機組同燈都由大樓上熄滅時，呢個鬼標誌就顯露出咗嚟。\n\n粵興公司（ Yuet Hing Company ）曾經喺南京街15號嘅呢個地方經營電子秤、紙張、印刷產品和印刷服務。 它們仍然存在，但它們有向西移動大約七個街區，留低咗呢個由書法家黄祚瑁（黄伟昌或黄伟昌）書寫嘅標誌。\n\n黃教授出生於1901年或1902年，在中國書法界頗有名氣。 他於1993年去世，但佢嘅作品仍被香港藝術館收藏。 佢哋至少喺當地舉辦了三個展覽：“香港書法”（ 1990年）、“太乙樓收藏中國現代書畫”（ 1991年）和“墨紅香”（ 1999年）。\n\n教授似乎專門研究文書（文書），當有人想給人一種莊重或舊世界的感覺時，香港的標牌往往會使用這種字體。 可能偏愛Clerical Script嘅企業和機構係學校、文具店，或者仲有印刷商。\n\n或者悅興公司嘅東主認為黃教授嘅平衡書法非常適合為佢哋嘅音阶做廣告？','\n',char(10)),1,'高基大廈佐敦道9號油尖旺區',1,'{"buildingName":"高基大廈","buildingNumberFrom":"9","buildingNumberTo":"11","streetName":"佐敦道","neighbourhood":"油麻地","district":"油尖旺區","region":"九龍","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('emqJbsDvxCqX','zh-hans','''悦兴公司''',1,replace('一家餐厅和一家 Prizemart 关门了，当他们所有的空调机组和灯都从大楼上熄灭时，这个鬼标志就显露出来了。\n\n粵興公司 （Yuet Hing Company） 曾经在南京街 15 号的这个地方经营电子秤、纸张、印刷产品和印刷服务。它们仍然存在，但它们已经向西移动了大约七个街区，留下了这个由书法家黄維瑁（黄伟昌或黄伟昌）书写的标志。\n\n黄教授出生于 1901 年或 1902 年，在中国书法界颇有名气。他于 1993 年去世，但他的作品仍被香港艺术馆收藏。他们至少在当地举办了三个展览：“香港书法”（1990 年）、“太乙楼收藏中国现代书画”（1991 年）和“墨红香”（1999 年）。\n\n教授似乎专门研究文书 （文书），当有人想给人一种庄重或旧世界的感觉时，香港的标牌往往会使用这种字体。可能偏爱 Clerical Script 的企业和机构是学校、文具店，也许还有印刷商。\n\n也许悦兴公司的东主认为黄教授的平衡书法非常适合为他们的音阶做广告？','\n',char(10)),1,'高基大厦佐敦道9号油尖旺区',1,'{"buildingName":"高基大厦","buildingNumberFrom":"9","buildingNumberTo":"11","streetName":"佐敦道","neighbourhood":"油麻地","district":"油尖旺区","region":"九龙","country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('5NIqTHH_BLHE','en','Portuguese Community Schools',0,replace('The Portuguese were pioneers in Hong Kong, operating on this coast long before the British arrived.\n\nPlaying an important role in the maritime history of Hong Kong, the Portuguese can even claim a legitimate contribution to that most Hong Kong of icons, sailing junks, which might be more accurately classed as ‘lorchas’ - sailing vessels with Cantonese style sails on Portuguese hulls.\n\nAttesting to their long association, the Portuguese Lusitano Club is one of the oldest clubs in Hong Kong.\n\nThe Portuguese also gave Hong Kong some of its early architecture and were among the first to build themselves houses in Kowloon after it became British.\n\nFittingly, we found this Ghost Sign for Portuguese Community Schools, Inc., or Escola Camões, here in Jordan.\n\nFounded in the 1950s, Escola Camões was taken over by Po Leung Kuk and in 1999 it was re-named Po Leung Kuk Camões Tan Siu Lin Primary School. Sadly it is shut now but its Ghost Sign still adorns a small entrance up a flight of stairs. The yellow school house, ominously quiet, is now a popular destination for urban explorers.\n\nOther than ships, architecture, and schools, the Portuguese have also made countless contributions to Hong Kong’s vernacular. ‘Praya,’ for example, is Portuguese for promenade. ‘Mandarin’ is a giver of mandates. A ‘comprador’ is a provider, an ‘amah’ is a nurse and ‘joss’ as in ‘joss stick’ comes from the Portuguese word for god - deus.','\n',char(10)),0,'5 Cox''s Rd, Yau Ma Tei',1,'{"buildingName":"Emperor Height","buildingNumberFrom":"5","streetName":"Cox''s Road","neighbourhood":"Yau Ma Tei","district":"YTM","region":"KL","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('5NIqTHH_BLHE','zh-hant','葡萄牙社區學校',1,replace('葡萄牙人係香港嘅先驅，早喺英國人到來之前就已經喺香港海岸活動。\n\n葡萄牙人在香港的航海史上扮演著重要的角色，甚至可以聲稱對香港最標誌性的帆船做出了合法的貢獻，這些帆船可能更準確地歸類為“lorchas”——在葡萄牙船體上帶有粵式風帆的帆船。\n\n葡萄牙卢西塔诺俱樂部係香港歷史最悠久嘅俱樂部之一，係佢哋悠久嘅合作。\n\n葡萄牙人仲為香港提供埋啲早期建築，並且係成為英國人後最早喺九龍建造房屋嘅人之一。\n\n恰如其分地，我哋喺約旦搵到咗呢個Portuguese Community Schools，Inc.或Escola Camões嘅鬼標誌。\n\nEscola Camões成立於1950年代，之後由保良局接管，並於1999年更名為保良局Camões陈兆莲小學。 可惜嘅係，它而家有關閉，但它的幽靈標誌仍然裝飾住一段樓梯上嘅一個小入口。 黃色嘅校舍，不祥的寧靜，而家係城市探險家嘅熱門目的地。\n\n除了船隻、建築同學校，葡萄牙人仲為香港嘅方言做出了無數貢獻。 例如，“Praya”在葡萄牙語中是散步的意思。 “普通話”係命令嘅賦予者。 “comparador”係提供者，“amah”係護士，“joss”中嘅“joss”來自葡萄牙語中嘅上帝- deus。','\n',char(10)),1,'御景臺覺士道5號油尖旺區',1,'{"buildingName":"御景臺","buildingNumberFrom":"5","streetName":"覺士道","neighbourhood":"油麻地","district":"油尖旺區","region":"九龍","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('5NIqTHH_BLHE','zh-hans','葡萄牙社区学校',1,replace('葡萄牙人是香港的先驱，早在英国人到来之前就已经在香港海岸活动。\n\n葡萄牙人在香港的航海史上扮演着重要的角色，甚至可以声称对香港最标志性的帆船做出了合法的贡献，这些帆船可能更准确地归类为“lorchas”——在葡萄牙船体上带有粤式风帆的帆船。\n\n葡萄牙卢西塔诺俱乐部是香港历史最悠久的俱乐部之一，是他们悠久的合作。\n\n葡萄牙人还为香港提供了一些早期建筑，并且是成为英国人后最早在九龙建造房屋的人之一。\n\n恰如其分地，我们在约旦找到了这个 Portuguese Community Schools， Inc. 或 Escola Camões 的鬼标志。\n\nEscola Camões 成立于 1950 年代，后由保良局接管，并于 1999 年更名为保良局 Camões 陈兆莲小学。遗憾的是，它现在已经关闭了，但它的幽灵标志仍然装饰着一段楼梯上的一个小入口。黄色的校舍，不祥的宁静，现在是城市探险家的热门目的地。\n\n除了船只、建筑和学校，葡萄牙人还为香港的方言做出了无数贡献。例如，“Praya”在葡萄牙语中是散步的意思。“普通话”是命令的赋予者。“comparador”是提供者，“amah”是护士，“joss”中的“joss”来自葡萄牙语中的上帝 - deus。','\n',char(10)),1,'御景台觉士道5号油尖旺区',1,'{"buildingName":"御景台","buildingNumberFrom":"5","streetName":"觉士道","neighbourhood":"油麻地","district":"油尖旺区","region":"九龙","country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('GYiZH8H_7hEH','en','Chu''s Jade Manufactured',0,replace('A little tenement building stands on a quiet backstreet in Tsim Sha Tsui. Its ground floor is boarded up but the Ghost Sign above its door still reads clearly, despite having lost about a quarter of its letters - “Chu’s Jade Manufacturer.”\n\nHKTDC still lists Chu’s as a “verified and credible” supplier, trader and manufacturer of fine jewellery, loose stones and raw materials. If it is, then business is carrying on somewhere else - this old sign is a goner.\n\nChu’s must have been something in its day. Founded in 1962, one piece from the shop, a rock crystal necklace on a knotted silk cord, can be found in the 20th Century collection of the British Museum.\n\nCommissioned in 2006, by the noted Tiffany & Co. and Halston designer Elsa Peretti, the necklace is hardly ancient but alongside Chu’s it has a place in Hong Kong’s history of jewellery.\n\nDominated by the Hong Kong - Burma jade trade, the manufacturing and trading of jade is one of Hong Kong’s oldest businesses. The industry faced hard times when the U.S. imposed an embargo on HK jadeite goods in 1965 but lobbying from the HK Jade & Stone Manufacturer’s Association meant that jade exports from the city resumed in 1967 with certificates of origin bearing those magic words: “Made in Hong Kong.”\n\nWe hope Chu’s is carrying on that legacy somewhere else but if not, its Ghost Sign still tells its glamorous tale.','\n',char(10)),0,'1 B Kimberley St, Tsim Sha Tsui',1,'{"buildingName":"Everglory Centre","buildingNumberFrom":"1B","streetName":"Kimberley Street","neighbourhood":"Tsim Sha Tsui","district":"YTM","region":"KL","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('GYiZH8H_7hEH','zh-hant','楚氏玉石製造',1,replace('一棟小唐樓矗立喺尖沙咀一條靜嘅後街上。 它的一樓被木板封住，但門上的鬼牌仍然清晰地寫著——“Chu''s Jade Maker”。\n\n香港貿發局仍將Chu''s列為“經驗證和可信”嘅高級珠寶、裸石和原材料的供應商、貿易商和製造商。 如果係咁，咁生意就喺其他地方進行——呢個老牌子已經死咗。\n\nChu''s喺嗰個時代一定好受歡迎。 呢間舖頭成立於1962年，其中一件來自舖頭嘅作品係一條打結嘅絲線上嘅水晶頸鏈，可以喺大英博物館嘅20世紀收藏中搵到。\n\n2006年，由著名嘅蒂芙尼&公司同哈爾斯頓設計師艾尔莎·佩雷蒂委託製作，條頸鏈並不古老，但與朱氏嘅頸鏈一樣，佢喺香港嘅珠寶歷史上佔有一席之地。\n\n玉石嘅製造和貿易以港緬玉貿易為主，係香港歷史最悠久嘅行業之一。 當美國在1965年對香港的翡翠商品實施禁運時，該行業面臨困難時期，但香港玉石製造商協會的游說意味著該市的玉石出口在1967年恢復了，其原產地證書上寫著那些神奇的詞語：“香港製造”。\n\n我哋希望Chu''s喺其他地方繼承遺產，但如果冇，它的Ghost Sign仍然講述住它迷人嘅故仔。','\n',char(10)),1,'恆港中心金巴利街1B號油尖旺區',1,'{"buildingName":"恆港中心","buildingNumberFrom":"1B","streetName":"金巴利街","neighbourhood":"尖沙咀","district":"油尖旺區","region":"九龍","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('GYiZH8H_7hEH','zh-hans','楚氏玉石制造',1,replace('一栋小唐楼矗立在尖沙咀一条安静的后街上。它的一楼被木板封住，但门上的鬼牌仍然清晰地写着——“Chu''s Jade Maker”。\n\n香港贸发局仍将 Chu''s 列为“经验证和可信”的高级珠宝、裸石和原材料的供应商、贸易商和制造商。如果是这样，那么生意就在别的地方进行——这个老牌子已经死了。\n\nChu''s 在那个时代一定很受欢迎。这家商店成立于 1962 年，其中一件来自商店的作品是一条打结的丝线上的水晶项链，可以在大英博物馆的 20 世纪收藏中找到。\n\n2006年，由著名的蒂芙尼&公司和哈尔斯顿设计师艾尔莎·佩雷蒂委托制作，这条项链并不古老，但与朱氏的项链一样，它在香港的珠宝历史上占有一席之地。\n\n玉石的制造和贸易以港缅玉贸易为主，是香港历史最悠久的行业之一。当美国在1965年对香港的翡翠商品实施禁运时，该行业面临困难时期，但香港玉石制造商协会的游说意味着该市的玉石出口在1967年恢复了，其原产地证书上写着那些神奇的词语：“香港制造”。\n\n我们希望 Chu''s 在其他地方继承这一遗产，但如果没有，它的 Ghost Sign 仍然讲述着它迷人的故事。','\n',char(10)),1,'恒港中心金巴利街1B号油尖旺区',1,'{"buildingName":"恒港中心","buildingNumberFrom":"1B","streetName":"金巴利街","neighbourhood":"尖沙咀","district":"油尖旺区","region":"九龙","country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('suM2omlbEs9C','en','Snow White Studio',0,replace('Someday my prints will come...\n\nBut maybe not from Snow White, yet another photo studio Ghost Sign we''ve been keeping an eye on in Hong Kong.\n\nSadly, Snow White Studio has had its lettering and Kai script signage removed from the façade of this Wanchai building in recent months.\n\nThere''s no saving this beauty... 😓🍎','\n',char(10)),0,'113 Wan Chai Rd, Wan Chai',1,'{"buildingName":"Tak Lee Commercial Building","buildingNumberFrom":"113","streetName":"Wan Chai Road","neighbourhood":"Wan Chai","district":"WC","region":"HK","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('suM2omlbEs9C','zh-hant','白雪公主工作室',1,replace('總有日，我嘅印刷品會嚟......\n\n但或者唔係來自白雪公主，係我哋一直關注緊嘅另一家喺香港嘅攝影工作室Ghost Sign。\n\n可惜嘅係，近幾個月嚟，白雪公主工作室嘅字體同Kai腳本標牌已由這座灣仔大樓嘅外牆被移除。\n\n冇辦法拯救呢個靚...... 😓🍎','\n',char(10)),1,'得利商業大廈灣仔道113號灣仔區',1,'{"buildingName":"得利商業大廈","buildingNumberFrom":"113","streetName":"灣仔道","neighbourhood":"灣仔","district":"灣仔區","region":null,"country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('suM2omlbEs9C','zh-hans','白雪公主工作室',1,replace('总有一天，我的印刷品会来......\n\n但也许不是来自白雪公主，这是我们一直在关注的另一家在香港的摄影工作室 Ghost Sign。\n\n遗憾的是，近几个月来，白雪公主工作室的字体和 Kai 脚本标牌已从这座湾仔大楼的外墙被移除。\n\n没有办法拯救这个美丽......😓🍎','\n',char(10)),1,'得利商业大厦湾仔道113号湾仔区',1,'{"buildingName":"得利商业大厦","buildingNumberFrom":"113","streetName":"湾仔道","neighbourhood":"湾仔","district":"湾仔区","region":null,"country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('gPLYKin9prQG','en','Tsang Lee Kee Co.',0,NULL,0,'288 Lockhart Rd, Wan Chai',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"288","streetName":"Lockhart Road","neighbourhood":"Wan Chai","district":"WC","region":"HK","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('gPLYKin9prQG','zh-hant','曾利記公司',1,NULL,0,'駱克道288號灣仔區',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"288","streetName":"駱克道","neighbourhood":"灣仔","district":"灣仔區","region":null,"country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('gPLYKin9prQG','zh-hans','曾利记公司',1,NULL,0,'骆克道288号湾仔区',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"288","streetName":"骆克道","neighbourhood":"湾仔","district":"湾仔区","region":null,"country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('63hCs3Btbgv3','en','Kent Cigarett Advert',0,replace('Tobacco advertising has been banned in Hong Kong since 1997 but this giant Ghost Sign for Kent cigarettes in Causeway Bay is beginning to rear its head again.\n\nNamed for Herbert Kent, an executive at the Lorillard Tobacco Company, Kent is mostly known as the first popular filtered cigarette.\n\nIn the early 1950s, cigarettes were mostly filterless but it was starting to dawn on consumers that smoking might be bad for their health.\n\nEnter Kent with its "famous micronite filter," promising its consumers the "greatest health protection in history."\n\nIt''s a shame those filters were full of asbestos...\n\nCheck out our story for Zolima Citymag, ''The Toxic Legacy of Cigarette Ads'' on the history of tobacco advertising in Hong Kong and how they got ghosted by one determined doctor','\n',char(10)),0,'169 Gloucester Rd, Wan Chai',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"169","streetName":"Gloucester Road","neighbourhood":"Wan Chai","district":"WC","region":"HK","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('63hCs3Btbgv3','zh-hant','Kent Cigarett廣告',1,replace('自1997年以來，香港一直禁止煙草廣告，但銅鑼灣呢個巨大嘅肯特香煙鬼標誌又開始抬頭咗。\n\nKent以Lorillard Tobacco Company嘅高管Herbert Kent嘅名命名，它最廣為人知嘅係第一種流行嘅過濾式香煙。\n\n在1950年代初期，香煙多數係無過濾嘴嘅，但消費者開始意識到食煙可能對他們的健康有害。\n\n肯特郡擁有“著名嘅micronite過濾器”，向消費者承諾提供“歷史上最偉大嘅健康保護”。\n\n可惜嗰啲過濾器度裝滿了石棉......\n\n閱讀我哋為Zolima Citymag撰寫嘅“香煙廣告嘅有毒遺產”故事，瞭解香港煙草廣告嘅歷史，以及它們如何被一位堅定嘅医师所忽視','\n',char(10)),1,'告士打道169號灣仔區',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"169","streetName":"告士打道","neighbourhood":"灣仔","district":"灣仔區","region":null,"country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('63hCs3Btbgv3','zh-hans','Kent Cigarett 广告',1,replace('自 1997 年以来，香港一直禁止烟草广告，但铜锣湾这个巨大的肯特香烟鬼标志又开始抬头了。\n\nKent 以 Lorillard Tobacco Company 的高管 Herbert Kent 的名字命名，它最广为人知的是第一种流行的过滤式香烟。\n\n在 1950 年代初期，香烟大多是无过滤嘴的，但消费者开始意识到吸烟可能对他们的健康有害。\n\n肯特郡拥有“著名的 micronite 过滤器”，向消费者承诺提供“历史上最伟大的健康保护”。\n\n可惜那些过滤器里装满了石棉......\n\n阅读我们为 Zolima Citymag 撰写的“香烟广告的有毒遗产”故事，了解香港烟草广告的历史，以及它们如何被一位坚定的医生所忽视','\n',char(10)),1,'告士打道169号湾仔区',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"169","streetName":"告士打道","neighbourhood":"湾仔","district":"湾仔区","region":null,"country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('_Na7YefqT7Lz','en','Dhl Express Service Point',0,NULL,0,'18 Che Kung Miu Rd, Tai Wai, Sha Tin',1,'{"buildingName":"Club House","buildingNumberFrom":"18","estateName":"The Pavilia Farm","streetName":"Che Kung Miu Road","neighbourhood":"Tai Wai, Sha Tin","district":"ST","region":"NT","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('_Na7YefqT7Lz','zh-hant','Dhl Express服務點',1,NULL,0,'會所柏傲莊車公廟路18號沙田區',1,'{"buildingName":"會所","buildingNumberFrom":"18","estateName":"柏傲莊","streetName":"車公廟路","district":"沙田區","region":"新界","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('_Na7YefqT7Lz','zh-hans','Dhl Express 服务点',1,NULL,0,'会所柏傲庄车公庙路18号沙田区',1,'{"buildingName":"会所","buildingNumberFrom":"18","estateName":"柏傲庄","streetName":"车公庙路","district":"沙田区","region":"新界","country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('Ei_yk5_-l3I_','en','Herbalist & Acupuncture Clinic',0,replace('English and Chinese text are in harmony with this Ghost Sign for Chung Wah Acupuncture & Herbalist Clinic. Making use of the flexibility afforded by Chinese text orientation, this handsome old sign lives on happily in Wanchai.\n\nTraditional Chinese Medicine is a medical system encompassing theories and practices of herbal medicine, acupuncture, acupressure, moxibustion, nutrition, massage, exercise, and meditation. It''s been used to diagnose, treat, and prevent illnesses for more than 2,000 years with the earliest writings on TCM dating from 200 BCE.\n\nBased on a belief in yin and yang, defined as opposing energies, such as earth and heaven, winter and summer, and happiness and sadness, the central idea behind TCM is one of achieving balance and flow with a life force known as ''qi''. When balance can be found, so can wellbeing.\n\nIn terms of Ghost Signs, our medicine is a balance between development and cultural preservation ⚖️.','\n',char(10)),0,'384 Lockhart Rd, Wan Chai',1,'{"buildingName":"Caine Mansion","buildingNumberFrom":"384","streetName":"Lockhart Road","neighbourhood":"Wan Chai","district":"WC","region":"HK","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('Ei_yk5_-l3I_','zh-hant','草藥師和針灸診所',1,replace('英文同中文文本與呢個Chung Wah針灸同草藥診所嘅鬼標誌相協調。 利用中文文本方向嘅靈活性，呢個靚嘅舊標誌喺灣仔快樂地生活住。\n\n中醫是一門涵蓋草藥、針灸、穴位按摩、艾灸、營養學、按摩、運動和冥想理論和實踐的醫學系統。 它被用于診斷、治療和預防疾病已有2,000多年嘅歷史，最早嘅中醫著作可以追溯到公元前200年。\n\n基於對陰陽的信仰，陰陽被定義為對立的能量，如地與天、冬與夏、快樂與悲傷，中醫背後的中心思想是用一種被稱為“氣”的生命力實現平衡與流動。 当搵到平衡時，健康都可以。\n\n就鬼星座而言，我哋嘅藥物係發展同文化保護⚖️之間的平衡。','\n',char(10)),1,'嘉賢大廈駱克道384號灣仔區',1,'{"buildingName":"嘉賢大廈","buildingNumberFrom":"384","streetName":"駱克道","neighbourhood":"灣仔","district":"灣仔區","region":null,"country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('Ei_yk5_-l3I_','zh-hans','草药师和针灸诊所',1,replace('英文和中文文本与这个Chung Wah针灸和草药诊所的鬼标志相协调。利用中文文本方向的灵活性，这个漂亮的旧标志在湾仔快乐地生活着。\n\n中医是一门涵盖草药、针灸、穴位按摩、艾灸、营养学、按摩、运动和冥想理论和实践的医学系统。它被用于诊断、治疗和预防疾病已有 2,000 多年的历史，最早的中医著作可以追溯到公元前 200 年。\n\n基于对阴阳的信仰，阴阳被定义为对立的能量，如地与天、冬与夏、快乐与悲伤，中医背后的中心思想是用一种被称为 “气 ”的生命力实现平衡与流动。当找到平衡时，健康也可以。\n\n就鬼星座而言，我们的药物是发展和文化保护⚖️之间的平衡。','\n',char(10)),1,'嘉贤大厦骆克道384号湾仔区',1,'{"buildingName":"嘉贤大厦","buildingNumberFrom":"384","streetName":"骆克道","neighbourhood":"湾仔","district":"湾仔区","region":null,"country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('zRx9cgWfdobU','en','Marlboro Advert',0,replace('A tobacco-stained wall reveals Hong Kong''s not so distant past.\n\nNormally known for their idiosyncratic style and humanity, hand-painted signage is usually charming. There is an exception: hand-painted tobacco advertising - a leftover from the bad old days.\n\nBlink and you’ll miss this giant Marlboro Ghost Sign in Morrison Hill. Hidden in plain sight, it was audaciously painted several storeys high and would have been aimed perfectly at motorists coming out of the Aberdeen Tunnel onto the Wong Nai Chung Gap Flyover.\n\nRight up until the late 90s, tobacco advertising was completely normal and nobody would have thought it strange. “I can’t even think of a place where there wasn’t tobacco advertising, to tell the truth,” says Dr. Judith Mackay, international tobacco control advocate and senior policy advisor to the World Health Organisation. “It was absolutely everywhere. On buildings, on the Star Ferry, outside schools…”\n\nDr. Mackay and her colleagues spent years denormalising tobacco advertising with many of their efforts culminating in the Smoking (Public Health) Ordinance and its subsequent amendments. Tobacco advertising has been banned in Hong Kong since 1997 but this old Marlboro Ghost Sign is a reminder of the way things were and how they could still be - a jarring sight when you suddenly realise what you’re seeing.\n\nCheck out our story for Zolima Citymag, ''The Toxic Legacy of Tobacco Ads, on the history of tobacco advertising in Hong Kong and how they got ghosted by one determined doctor','\n',char(10)),0,'50 Morrison Hill Rd, Wan Chai',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"50","streetName":"Morrison Hill Road","neighbourhood":"Wan Chai","district":"WC","region":"HK","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('zRx9cgWfdobU','zh-hant','萬寶路廣告',1,replace('一面霑滿煙草嘅牆壁揭示了香港並不遙遠嘅過去。\n\n手繪標牌通常以其獨特嘅風格同人性而聞名，通常好迷人。 有一個例外：手繪煙草廣告-過去糟糕時光嘅遺留物。\n\n眨眼間，你會錯過摩里逊山嘅呢個巨大嘅萬寶路幽靈標誌。 它隱藏喺搶眼嘅地方，大膽咁畀粉刷成幾層樓高，完美地瞄準了由香港仔隧道出嚟進入黃泥涌峽天桥嘅駕車者。\n\n直到90年代後期，煙草廣告還是完全正常嘅，沒有人會覺得好奇怪。 “講真，我什至想不出一個冇煙草廣告嘅地方，”國際煙草控制倡導者兼世界衛生組織高級政策顧問Judith Mackay博士話。 “它絕對無處不在。 喺建築物上、喺天星小輪上、喺學校外面......唻\n\nMackay博士同佢嘅同事花了數年時間令煙草廣告非正常化，佢哋嘅好多努力最終導致了《食煙（公共衛生）條例》及其隨後嘅修正案。 自1997年以來，香港已禁止煙草廣告，但呢個古老嘅萬寶路幽靈標誌提醒住啲人事物嘅過去同未來——当你突然意識到你所睇到嘅係乜嘢時，係一個唔和諧嘅景象。\n\n請查閱我哋為Zolima Citymag撰寫嘅「煙草廣告嘅有毒遺產」嘅故仔，了解香港煙草廣告嘅歷史，以及煙草廣告如何被一位堅定嘅医师所困擾','\n',char(10)),1,'摩理臣山道50號灣仔區',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"50","streetName":"摩理臣山道","neighbourhood":"灣仔","district":"灣仔區","region":null,"country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('zRx9cgWfdobU','zh-hans','万宝路广告',1,replace('一面沾满烟草的墙壁揭示了香港并不遥远的过去。\n\n手绘标牌通常以其独特的风格和人性而闻名，通常很迷人。有一个例外：手绘烟草广告 - 过去糟糕时光的遗留物。\n\n眨眼间，你会错过莫里森山的这个巨大的万宝路幽灵标志。它隐藏在显眼的地方，大胆地被粉刷成几层楼高，完美地瞄准了从香港仔隧道出来进入黄泥涌峡立交桥的驾车者。\n\n直到 90 年代后期，烟草广告还是完全正常的，没有人会觉得这很奇怪。“说实话，我什至想不出一个没有烟草广告的地方，”国际烟草控制倡导者兼世界卫生组织高级政策顾问 Judith Mackay 博士说。“它绝对无处不在。在建筑物上、在天星小轮上、在学校外面......”\n\nMackay 博士和她的同事花了数年时间使烟草广告非正常化，他们的许多努力最终导致了《吸烟（公共卫生）条例》及其随后的修正案。自 1997 年以来，香港已禁止烟草广告，但这个古老的万宝路幽灵标志提醒着人们事物的过去和未来——当你突然意识到你所看到的是什么时，这是一个不和谐的景象。\n\n请查阅我们为 Zolima Citymag 撰写的「烟草广告的有毒遗产」的故事，了解香港烟草广告的历史，以及烟草广告如何被一位坚定的医生所困扰','\n',char(10)),1,'摩理臣山道50号湾仔区',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"50","streetName":"摩理臣山道","neighbourhood":"湾仔","district":"湾仔区","region":null,"country":"香港特区"}');
