INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('NeYyHdEZFKE1','en','''Ling Ling Fashion''',0,replace('This is just a trace of signage left behind, like an after-image burned into the retina and the memory. Remaining long after the original character has vanished these signs are traces of the sign’s original characters which were likely made of plastic or metal. When these characters are removed they reveal the signboard’s original colour from before it got sunbleached. Sometimes the trace is nothing more than leftover glue, still clinging to the signboard backing.\n\nThese types of Ghost Signs are very common in Hong Kong and are what Gary Warnaby and Dominic Medway call ‘revenant signs’ in their essay, Ghost Fascias.\n\nEven less substantial than ghost signs, these artifacts are just trace impressions of grime and sun bleached negatives leaving silhouettes in empty space like chalk outlines at the scene of a murder. Whereas signage is meant to communicate certain messages, these revenant signs are an unintended or unintentional communication. They live “a branding half-life” as “revenants in the urban retail landscape” and serve as “a reminder that no organisation is immune from the vicissitudes of economic and social change.”\n\nIn Hong Kong’s challenging fiscal climate, revenant signs are all too common as small businesses bear the brunt of economic hardship with consumers moving away from neighbourhood stores to larger shops, chain stores, online channels and bulk retailers from just across the border in Mainland China. \n\nSometimes left for years, these abandoned signboards and revenant signs look truly desperate as they drown in ‘To Let’ posters. “The economic effect of higher retail vacancies has inevitably been significant. However there is also an aesthetic impact,” write Warnaby and Medway. “Empty shops are a very visible sign of recession and seriously damage consumer confidence,” writes Esther Addley in her 2009 article for the Guardian, ''Empty, unlet and unloved: the new British high street.''  She compares these vacancies to “rotten gaps in the civic smile.” These remnants of shop fascias which identify previous occupants of vacant shops reveal once important components of grassroots communities. These revenant signs are a fleeting record of what came before.','\n',char(10)),0,'101 Shau Kei Wan Main St East, Shau Kei Wan',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"19","estateName":"Shaukeiwan Government Primary School","streetName":"Shau Kei Wan Main Street East","neighbourhood":"Shau Kei Wan","district":"EST","region":"HK","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('NeYyHdEZFKE1','zh-hant','''Ling Ling時尚''',1,replace('只係留低嘅一絲標牌，就好似烙印喺視網膜和記憶中嘅殘影。 這些標誌在原始字符消失後仍然存在很長時間，是標誌原始字符的痕跡，很可能是由塑膠或金屬製成的。 当呢啲字符被移除時，它們會露出招牌喺被曬白之前嘅原始顏色。 有時，痕只不過係殘留嘅膠水，仍然粘喺招牌背襯上。\n\n這些類型的鬼星座在香港非常常見，Gary Warnaby和Dominic Medway在他們的文章《鬼筋膜》中稱之為“亡魂星座”。\n\n呢啲文物甚至不如幽靈標誌咁重要，它們只是污垢和陽光漂白嘅底片嘅痕迹，在空白中留下剪影，就好似謀殺現場嘅粉筆輪廓一樣。 標牌旨在傳達某些信息，而呢啲亡靈標誌則係無意或無意嘅交流。 佢哋作為“城市零售領域嘅亡魂”過住“品牌半衰期”，並“提醒我哋，冇組織能夠倖免於經濟和社會變革嘅變遷”。\n\n喺香港充滿挑戰嘅財政環境中，隨著消費者由社區商店轉向中國大陸邊境對面嘅大型商店、連鎖店、在線渠道和大宗零售商，小企業首當其衝地承受住經濟困難嘅迹象。 \n\n呢啲廢棄嘅招牌同亡魂招牌有時被遺棄多年，当它們淹沒喺xTo Let徜徉海報中時，睇嚟真係好絕望。 占零售空置率上升的經濟影響不可避免地係巨大嘅。 然而，都具有審美影響，“Warnaby同Medway寫道。 “空盪盪的商店是經濟衰退的一個非常明顯的跡象，嚴重損害了消費者的信心，”埃斯特·阿德利（Esther Addley）在2009年為《衛報》撰寫的文章中寫道，“空蕩蕩的、不出租的和不受歡迎的：新的英國商業街”。  佢將呢啲職位空缺比作“公民微笑中嘅腐爛差距”。 呢啲舖頭楣板嘅殘餘物可以識別空置舖頭嘅前住戶，揭示了草根社區曾經嘅重要組成部分。 呢啲亡魂嘅迹象係之前事物嘅短暫記錄。','\n',char(10)),1,'筲箕灣官立小學筲箕灣東大街19號東區',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"19","estateName":"筲箕灣官立小學","streetName":"筲箕灣東大街","neighbourhood":"筲箕灣","district":"東區","region":null,"country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('NeYyHdEZFKE1','zh-hans','''Ling Ling 时尚''',1,replace('这只是留下的一丝标牌，就像烙印在视网膜和记忆中的残影。这些标志在原始字符消失后仍然存在很长时间，是标志原始字符的痕迹，很可能是由塑料或金属制成的。当这些字符被移除时，它们会露出招牌在被晒白之前的原始颜色。有时，痕迹只不过是残留的胶水，仍然粘在招牌背衬上。\n\n这些类型的鬼星座在香港非常常见，Gary Warnaby 和 Dominic Medway 在他们的文章《鬼筋膜》中称之为“亡魂星座”。\n\n这些文物甚至不如幽灵标志那么重要，它们只是污垢和阳光漂白的底片的痕迹，在空白中留下剪影，就像谋杀现场的粉笔轮廓一样。标牌旨在传达某些信息，而这些亡灵标志则是无意或无意的交流。他们作为“城市零售领域的亡魂”过着“品牌半衰期”，并“提醒我们，没有组织能够幸免于经济和社会变革的变迁”。\n\n在香港充满挑战的财政环境中，随着消费者从社区商店转向中国大陆边境对面的大型商店、连锁店、在线渠道和大宗零售商，小企业首当其冲地承受着经济困难的迹象。\n\n这些废弃的招牌和亡魂招牌有时被遗弃多年，当它们淹没在“To Let”海报中时，看起来真的很绝望。“零售空置率上升的经济影响不可避免地是巨大的。然而，这也具有审美影响，“Warnaby 和 Medway 写道。“空荡荡的商店是经济衰退的一个非常明显的迹象，严重损害了消费者的信心，”埃斯特·阿德利 （Esther Addley） 在 2009 年为《卫报》撰写的文章中写道，“空荡荡的、不出租的和不受欢迎的：新的英国商业街”。 她将这些职位空缺比作“公民微笑中的腐烂差距”。这些商店楣板的残余物可以识别空置商店的前住户，揭示了草根社区曾经的重要组成部分。这些亡魂的迹象是之前事物的短暂记录。','\n',char(10)),1,'筲箕湾官立小学筲箕湾东大街19号东区',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"19","estateName":"筲箕湾官立小学","streetName":"筲箕湾东大街","neighbourhood":"筲箕湾","district":"东区","region":null,"country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('Mo3RyIYauM9C','en','ATV',0,replace('We couldn’t miss this classic urbex site with its massive Ghost Sign in Sai Kung.\n\nOnce a dye works, this multi-storey factory building in the village of Ho Chung became a television studio for ATV (Asia TV), formerly one of Hong Kong’s two terrestrial TV stations. TV in Hong Kong has always had its charms and, to be frank, ATV was the second best in a two-horse race.\n\nThe debt-ridden ATV really began its ignominious decline in 2011 when the station wrongly reported the death of former Chinese President, Jiang Zemin. In 2015, their broadcast licence wasn’t renewed and the station ended over-the-air transmission a year later.\n\nThe studio was abandoned in 2007, long before this controversy. That said, it’s had quite the afterlife, with many claiming that the building is haunted.\n\nWe’re not gonna lie - we may have heard some strange noises coming from the building along with remnants of Hell Money scattered about…\n\nWe concede that there could be perfectly rational explanations for the spooky sounds as the building has seen plenty of human activity over the years. It’s a regular haunt for graffiti artists and, in 2015, the studio entered the limelight once again as the site of an alleged bomb-making plot. 10 people were held on suspicion of using the old dye works for storing bomb making chemicals.\n\nMaybe it’s time to revive HK television by shooting a ghost story here…','\n',char(10)),0,'108 Luk Mei Tsuen, Sai Kung',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"108","streetName":"Luk Mei Tsuen","neighbourhood":"Sai Kung","district":"SK","region":"NT","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('Mo3RyIYauM9C','zh-hant','亞視',1,replace('我哋唔可以錯過呢個經典嘅urbex網站，它喺西貢有巨大嘅Ghost Sign。\n\n這座位於蠔涌村嘅多層工廠大樓曾經係染料厂，後來成為ATV （亞洲電視）嘅電視縯播室，ATV （亞洲電視台）曾是香港兩家地面電視台之一。 香港嘅電視一直都有它的魅力，坦率地說，亞視係兩匹馬比賽中嘅第二好。\n\n負債纍纍的亞視真正開始咗可恥嘅衰落係喺2011年，當時該電台錯誤咁報道咗中國前囯傢主蓆江澤民嘅去世。 2015年，佢哋嘅廣播許可證冇更新，該電台喺一年後結束咗無線傳輸。\n\n該工作室於2007年被廢棄，早喺呢場爭議之前。 也就是說，它有相當長嘅來世，好多人聲稱這座建築鬧鬼。\n\n我哋唔會講大話-我哋可能有聽到建築物傳來一些奇怪嘅聲，仲有散落喺各處嘅地獄之錢嘅殘餘物......\n\n我們承認，對於呢啲詭異嘅聲，可能有完全合理嘅解釋，因為多年來這座建築有見證大量嘅人類活動。 係塗鴉藝術家經常出沒嘅地方，2015年，該工作室再次成為人們關注的焦點，因為據稱係炸彈製造陰謀嘅發生地。 10人因涉嫌使用舊染料厂儲存炸彈製造化學品而被拘留。\n\n或者係時候喺呢度拍攝一個鬼故事嚟重振香港電視咗......','\n',char(10)),1,'鹿尾村108號西貢區',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"108","streetName":"鹿尾村","neighbourhood":"西貢","district":"西貢區","region":"新界","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('Mo3RyIYauM9C','zh-hans','亚视',1,replace('我们不能错过这个经典的 urbex 网站，它在西贡有巨大的 Ghost Sign。\n\n这座位于蚝涌村的多层工厂大楼曾经是染料厂，后来成为 ATV（亚洲电视）的电视演播室，ATV（亚洲电视台）曾是香港两家地面电视台之一。香港的电视一直都有它的魅力，坦率地说，亚视是两匹马比赛中的第二好。\n\n负债累累的亚视真正开始了可耻的衰落是在 2011 年，当时该电台错误地报道了中国前国家主席江泽民的去世。2015 年，他们的广播许可证没有更新，该电台在一年后结束了无线传输。\n\n该工作室于 2007 年被废弃，早在这场争议之前。也就是说，它有相当长的来世，许多人声称这座建筑闹鬼。\n\n我们不会撒谎 - 我们可能已经听到了建筑物传来一些奇怪的声音，还有散落在各处的地狱之钱的残余物......\n\n我们承认，对于这些诡异的声音，可能有完全合理的解释，因为多年来这座建筑已经见证了大量的人类活动。这是涂鸦艺术家经常出没的地方，2015 年，该工作室再次成为人们关注的焦点，因为据称是炸弹制造阴谋的发生地。10 人因涉嫌使用旧染料厂储存炸弹制造化学品而被拘留。\n\n也许是时候在这里拍摄一个鬼故事来重振香港电视了......','\n',char(10)),1,'鹿尾村108号西贡区',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"108","streetName":"鹿尾村","neighbourhood":"西贡","district":"西贡区","region":"新界","country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('aSXCp1LHk-XO','en','Shaw Studios',0,replace('Quiet on set!\n\nHong Kong and movies - it’s hard to imagine one without the other. Our cinematic city has it all from noirish crime thrillers to dream-like art house romances and of course high flying martial arts spectacles.\n\nThe 1950s were quite the time to be in the HK movie business and Shaw Brothers was at the centre of it. In 1961 Run Run Shaw, opened Movietown studio complex in Clearwater Bay - see the second photo for what it used to look like.\n\nMovietown was the largest and best-equipped studio in Chinese filmmaking and also the largest privately owned studio in the world. At its height Movietown had 15 stages, two permanent sets, and 1,300 employees - it wasn’t called Asia’s Hollywood for nothing!\n\nShaw Studio played a major role in popularising kung fu movies with titles like 1967’s One Armed Swordsman and 1978’s The 36th Chamber of Shaolin but those heady days couldn’t last forever.\n\nAfter the golden age of the 80s and 90s, Shaw Brothers faced increasing competition from Hollywood, local rivals like Golden Harvest, and a revived Chinese film industry. Rampant piracy didn’t help.\n\nShaw Brothers shifted focus to television production and, from 2000, operations were moved to Tseung Kwan O. Movietown was abandoned.\n\nVisiting one misty day, we could see there were still people living in the studio accommodation but they’ll be moved along soon. There are plans afoot to redevelop this Grade One Historical Structure into a complex of 14 storey villas and 23 apartment buildings with recreational facilities, a club house and a car park.\n\nSadly, in this town it’s here today, gone tomorrow. That’s show business!','\n',char(10)),0,'677 Clear Water Bay Rd, Clear Water Bay, Sai Kung',1,'{"buildingName":"Block A","buildingNumberFrom":"328","estateName":"328 Clear Water Bay Road","streetName":"Clear Water Bay Road","neighbourhood":"Clear Water Bay, Sai Kung","district":"SK","region":"NT","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('aSXCp1LHk-XO','zh-hant','邵氏影城',1,replace('片場好靜！\n\n香港同電影-好難想象一個冇另一個。 我哋嘅電影之城應有盡有，由黑色犯罪驚悚片到夢幻般嘅藝術浪漫片，梗係仲有高空飛行嘅武術奇觀。\n\n1950年代係進入香港電影業嘅好時機，邵氏兄弟係其中嘅中心。 1961年，Run Run Shaw喺剋利爾沃特灣開設了Movietown工作室綜合體-請參閱第二張照片，了解它過去個樣。\n\nMovietown係中國電影製作中規模最大、設備最齊全嘅工作室，都係世間上最大嘅私營工作室。 在鼎盛時期，Movietown擁有15個舞台、兩個永久佈景同1,300名員工-它被稱為亞洲荷里活並非無厘頭！\n\n邵氏工作室喺普及功夫電影方面發揮了重要作用，例如1967年嘅《獨臂刀》同1978年嘅《少林三十六房》，但嗰啲令人陶醉嘅日子並無永遠持續落去。\n\n喺80年代同90年代嘅黃金時代之後，邵氏兄弟面臨著來自荷里活、嘉禾等本地競爭對手以及復興嘅中國電影業嘅日益激烈的競爭。 猖獗嘅翻版都無濟於事。\n\n邵氏兄弟把重心轉移到電視製作上，從2000年起，業務轉移到將軍澳。\n\n喺一個霧懞懞嘅日子度，我哋可以睇到仍然有人住喺工作室嘅住宿中，但佢哋好快就會被搬走。 目前正計劃把這座一級歷史建築重建為一個由14層別墅同23棟公寓樓組成嘅綜合體，並設有娛樂設施、俱樂部會所同停車場。\n\n可悲嘅係，喺呢個小鎮上，它今日喺呢度，聽日就消失了。 就係演藝界！','\n',char(10)),1,'Ａ座清水灣道３２８號清水灣道328號西貢區',1,'{"buildingName":"Ａ座","buildingNumberFrom":"328","estateName":"清水灣道３２８號","streetName":"清水灣道","district":"西貢區","region":"新界","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('aSXCp1LHk-XO','zh-hans','邵氏影城',1,replace('片场很安静！\n\n香港和电影 - 很难想象一个没有另一个。我们的电影之城应有尽有，从黑色犯罪惊悚片到梦幻般的艺术浪漫片，当然还有高空飞行的武术奇观。\n\n1950 年代是进入香港电影业的好时机，邵氏兄弟是其中的中心。1961 年，Run Run Shaw 在克利尔沃特湾开设了 Movietown 工作室综合体 - 请参阅第二张照片，了解它过去的样子。\n\nMovietown 是中国电影制作中规模最大、设备最齐全的工作室，也是世界上最大的私营工作室。在鼎盛时期，Movietown 拥有 15 个舞台、两个永久布景和 1,300 名员工 - 它被称为亚洲好莱坞并非没有道理！\n\n邵氏工作室在普及功夫电影方面发挥了重要作用，例如 1967 年的《独臂刀》和 1978 年的《少林三十六房》，但那些令人陶醉的日子并没有永远持续下去。\n\n在 80 年代和 90 年代的黄金时代之后，邵氏兄弟面临着来自好莱坞、嘉禾等本地竞争对手以及复兴的中国电影业的日益激烈的竞争。猖獗的盗版也无济于事。\n\n邵氏兄弟将重心转移到电视制作上，从 2000 年起，业务转移到将军澳。\n\n在一个雾蒙蒙的日子里，我们可以看到仍然有人住在工作室的住宿中，但他们很快就会被搬走。目前正计划将这座一级历史建筑重建为一个由 14 层别墅和 23 栋公寓楼组成的综合体，并设有娱乐设施、俱乐部会所和停车场。\n\n可悲的是，在这个小镇上，它今天在这里，明天就消失了。这就是演艺界！','\n',char(10)),1,'a座清水湾道328号清水湾道328号西贡区',1,'{"buildingName":"a座","buildingNumberFrom":"328","estateName":"清水湾道328号","streetName":"清水湾道","district":"西贡区","region":"新界","country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('UJlJN5Dj68Th','en','The China Paint MFG.',0,replace('The China Paint Manufacturing Company was founded in 1932 in Mong Kok, by the Chinese American Lam Kun alongside the U.S. trained chemist, Liang Meng-tsi. That first year they came out with their Flower brand paint and exported it across South East Asia.\n\nChina Paint is one of the few Hong Kong paint manufacturers who survived the Japanese Occupation. Post war they set up in Kwun Tong, making automotive paints, primers and lacquers. (Camel Paint still operates in that neighborhood). By the 1960s China Paint were making paints for construction, metalware and plastic toys - just in time for Hong Kong’s boom in toy manufacturing.\n\nIn 1988 China Paint moved into a sprawling Sai Kung factory building but it wouldn’t stay long. Production moved to Shenzhen in 1991 and the Hong Kong facility has fallen silent.\n\nSo long, China Paint (as far as HK is concerned).','\n',char(10)),0,'9 Hong Ting Rd, Sai Kung',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"9","streetName":"Hong Ting Road","neighbourhood":"Sai Kung","district":"SK","region":"NT","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('UJlJN5Dj68Th','zh-hant','中國塗料製造公司。',1,replace('中國塗料製造公司於1932年由美籍華人Lam Kun與美國訓練有素的化學家Liang Meng-tsi喺旺角創立。 第一年，佢哋推出了Flower品牌塗料，並將其出口到東南亞。\n\n中國塗料係少數喺日本佔領時期倖存落嚟嘅香港塗料製造商之一。 戰後，佢哋喺觀塘成立，生產汽車油漆、底漆同油漆。 （ Camel Paint仍在該社區運營）。 到1960年代，中國塗料開始生產用于建築、金屬製品和塑料玩具嘅塗料——正好趕上香港玩具製造業嘅繁榮。\n\n1988年，中國塗料搬入咗一座龐大嘅西貢工廠大樓，但它並無停留太耐。 1991年，生產轉移到深圳，香港工廠從此陷入沉寂。\n\n一直以來，中國塗料（就香港而言）。','\n',char(10)),1,'康定路9號西貢區',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"9","streetName":"康定路","neighbourhood":"西貢","district":"西貢區","region":"新界","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('UJlJN5Dj68Th','zh-hans','中国涂料制造公司。',1,replace('中国涂料制造公司于 1932 年由美籍华人 Lam Kun 与美国训练有素的化学家 Liang Meng-tsi 在旺角创立。第一年，他们推出了 Flower 品牌涂料，并将其出口到东南亚。\n\n中国涂料是少数在日本占领时期幸存下来的香港涂料制造商之一。战后，他们在观塘成立，生产汽车油漆、底漆和油漆。（Camel Paint 仍在该社区运营）。到 1960 年代，中国涂料开始生产用于建筑、金属制品和塑料玩具的涂料——正好赶上香港玩具制造业的繁荣。\n\n1988 年，中国涂料搬进了一座庞大的西贡工厂大楼，但它并没有停留太久。1991 年，生产转移到深圳，香港工厂从此陷入沉寂。\n\n一直以来，中国涂料（就香港而言）。','\n',char(10)),1,'康定路9号西贡区',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"9","streetName":"康定路","neighbourhood":"西贡","district":"西贡区","region":"新界","country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('EM9cq3Rm4m35','en','''National Polyfoam Factory Ltd.''',0,replace('This old polystyrene factory in Sai Kung isn’t the hive of activity that it once was.\n\nAt time of recording, the two storey factory building was occupied partly by a co-working space, The Hive. The old industrial complex had also once been home to Castelo Concepts, whose banner was still hanging at the site when we visited. Castelo ran Jaspas, Wagyu Lounge, Piccolos and other well known local eateries but had to close many of its outlets when its founder, Wayne Parfitt, passed away in 2023.\n\nNational Polyfoam Factory Limited still exists as a company but as of recording, it operates out of Dongguan. Founded in 1977 at Tai Mong Tsai Road, this little factory is a bit of Sai Kung’s industrial past.\n\nThe National Polyfoam building has two ghost signs. The first faded sign, which reads “國際發泡膠廠” (the company’s name in Chinese) is pretty typical for the area. The other, with two colours and shadowing, looks almost like something you’d find in the States or Europe.\n\nSadly the products National manufactures, polystyrene boxes, sheets, insulation and packing peanuts, are not just in the past. Our shipping, construction, packaging and storage needs are still very much reliant on expanded polystyrene (EPS) foam products and they’ll be sticking around with us as non biodegradable waste long after these Ghost Signs have disappeared.','\n',char(10)),0,'5 Tai Mong Tsai Rd, Sai Kung',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"5","streetName":"Tai Mong Tsai Road","neighbourhood":"Sai Kung","district":"SK","region":"NT","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('EM9cq3Rm4m35','zh-hant','''National Polyfoam Factory Ltd.''（國家發泡膠廠有限公司）',1,replace('呢間位於西貢嘅舊聚苯乙烯工廠已今非昔比嘅熱鬧非凡。\n\n在錄音時，座兩層樓嘅廠房部分被一個聯合辦公空間The Hive佔據。 呢個古老嘅工業綜合體都曾經係Castelo Concepts嘅所在地，当我们參觀時，佢哋嘅橫幅仍然掛喺現場。 Castelo經營住Jaspas、Wagyu Lounge、Piccolos同其他當地知名餐館，但当其創始人Wayne Parfitt於2023年去世時，它不得不關閉好多分店。\n\nNational Polyfoam Factory Limited仍然作為一家公司存在，但截至記錄時，它在東莞開展業務。 呢間小工廠於1977年喺大旺仔道成立，有啲西貢嘅工業歷史。\n\nNational Polyfoam大樓有兩個幽靈標誌。 頭炮褪色嘅標誌上寫住“國際發泡膠廠”（公司嘅中文名稱），在該地區非常典型。 另一個有兩種顏色和陰影，看起來幾乎像你在美國或歐洲找到的東西。\n\n可惜嘅係，National生產嘅產品，聚苯乙烯盒、片材、絕緣材料同包裝花生，不僅僅昰過去。 我哋嘅運輸、建築、包裝和儲存需求仍然非常依賴發泡聚苯乙烯（ EPS ）泡沫產品，喺呢啲幽靈標誌消失後很長一段時間內，它們將作為不可生物降解嘅廢物留喺我哋身邊。','\n',char(10)),1,'大網仔路5號西貢區',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"5","streetName":"大網仔路","neighbourhood":"西貢","district":"西貢區","region":"新界","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('EM9cq3Rm4m35','zh-hans','''National Polyfoam Factory Ltd.'' （国家泡沫塑料厂有限公司）',1,replace('这家位于西贡的旧聚苯乙烯工厂已今非昔比的热闹非凡。\n\n在录音时，这座两层楼的厂房部分被一个联合办公空间 The Hive 占据。这个古老的工业综合体也曾经是 Castelo Concepts 的所在地，当我们参观时，他们的横幅仍然挂在现场。Castelo 经营着 Jaspas、Wagyu Lounge、Piccolos 和其他当地知名餐馆，但当其创始人 Wayne Parfitt 于 2023 年去世时，它不得不关闭许多分店。\n\nNational Polyfoam Factory Limited 仍然作为一家公司存在，但截至记录时，它在东莞开展业务。这家小工厂于 1977 年在大旺仔道成立，有点西贡的工业历史。\n\nNational Polyfoam 大楼有两个幽灵标志。第一个褪色的标志上写着 “國際發泡膠廠” （公司的中文名称），在该地区非常典型。另一个有两种颜色和阴影，看起来几乎像你在美国或欧洲找到的东西。\n\n遗憾的是，National 生产的产品，聚苯乙烯盒、片材、绝缘材料和包装花生，不仅仅是过去。我们的运输、建筑、包装和储存需求仍然非常依赖发泡聚苯乙烯 （EPS） 泡沫产品，在这些幽灵标志消失后很长一段时间内，它们将作为不可生物降解的废物留在我们身边。','\n',char(10)),1,'大网仔路5号西贡区',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"5","streetName":"大网仔路","neighbourhood":"西贡","district":"西贡区","region":"新界","country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('VAJhdEaxMvy3','en','Good Companion Cigarette Advert',0,replace('It’s quite jarring to see an ad for cigarettes these days - the practice was finally banned in the mid 90s, but once in a while we still catch glimpses of them in the form of Ghost Signs - a reminder of a darker past with some truly horrific advertising practices. These ads were everywhere and some of them, placed outside schools, were actually meant specifically to target kids. This one, completely painted over in white, is right next to a basketball court and around the corner from a playground.\n\nNormally we celebrate hand painted signs and mourn their loss but this time we’re doing things differently. We actually found and interviewed the person responsible for stubbing out tobacco advertising in Hong Kong and beyond. Check out the story in Zolima Citymag by Billy Potts, ''The Toxic Legacy of Cigarette Ads,'' to find out how Dr. Judith Mackay squared up against big tobacco in the 70s, 80s and 90s.\n\n“There were as many cigarette ads in the city as there were trees,” Mackay lamented. No more, thanks to the good Dr. and her team.','\n',char(10)),0,'14 Wan King Path, Sai Kung',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"14","streetName":"Wan King Path","neighbourhood":"Sai Kung","district":"SK","region":"NT","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('VAJhdEaxMvy3','zh-hant','Good Companion香煙廣告',1,replace('如今看到香煙廣告非常令人不安——呢種做法最終喺90年代中期被禁止，但偶爾我哋仍然會以幽靈標誌嘅形式瞥見它們——提醒人們更黑暗嘅過去，有啲真正可怕嘅廣告行為。 呢啲廣告無處不在，其中一些廣告放置喺學校外，實際上係專門針對兒童嘅。 呢個完全被涂成白色嘅屋就喺籃球場隔离，就在場嘅枴角处。\n\n通常我哋會慶祝手繪標誌並哀悼它們的損失，但今次我哋以不同的方式做事。 我哋實際上搵到並採訪咗負責喺香港及其他地區取締煙草廣告嘅人。 查看Billy Potts喺Zolima Citymag中嘅故仔“香煙廣告嘅有毒遺產”，瞭解Judith Mackay博士如何喺70年代、80年代同90年代對抗大型煙草公司。\n\n“城市入面有幾多樖樹，就有幾多個香煙廣告，”麦凯感嘆道。 多得咗好心嘅Dr.同佢嘅團隊，唔好再多咗。','\n',char(10)),1,'灣景街14號西貢區',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"14","streetName":"灣景街","neighbourhood":"西貢","district":"西貢區","region":"新界","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('VAJhdEaxMvy3','zh-hans','Good Companion 香烟广告',1,replace('如今看到香烟广告非常令人不安——这种做法最终在 90 年代中期被禁止，但偶尔我们仍然会以幽灵标志的形式瞥见它们——提醒人们更黑暗的过去，有一些真正可怕的广告行为。这些广告无处不在，其中一些广告放置在学校外，实际上是专门针对儿童的。这个完全被涂成白色的房子就在篮球场旁边，就在场的拐角处。\n\n通常我们会庆祝手绘标志并哀悼它们的损失，但这次我们以不同的方式做事。我们实际上找到并采访了负责在香港及其他地区取缔烟草广告的人。查看 Billy Potts 在 Zolima Citymag 中的故事“香烟广告的有毒遗产”，了解 Judith Mackay 博士如何在 70 年代、80 年代和 90 年代对抗大型烟草公司。\n\n“城市里有多少棵树，就有多少个香烟广告，”麦凯感叹道。多亏了好心的 Dr. 和她的团队，不要再多了。','\n',char(10)),1,'湾景街14号西贡区',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"14","streetName":"湾景街","neighbourhood":"西贡","district":"西贡区","region":"新界","country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('unvLyhWdWAb6','en','Skake Em Buns The Burger Shop',0,replace('A chef’s kiss to this burger-themed Ghost Sign.\n\nLong before the mid 2010s burger fad, Hong Kong had Shake ’em Buns - a fairly decent American themed burger joint that was a part of Hong Kong’s 2000s dining scene. Nostalgia may have something to do with this but we remember enjoying it.\n\nOne old Openrice review had this to say:\n“''Tis GOOOOOOOD.... The buns were fab, crispy on the outside and soft inside. [The] meat was flavourful, juicy and had the right texture, like what one would get with good, quality mince. There was just the right amount of crispy lettuce, tomato and onion.”\n\nThis was a place that enjoyed a little innuendo and the names of its menu items weren’t as tasteful as the burgers themselves - specials included “Happy Threesome,” “Debbie Does Dallas,” and “Missionary” - so we’re not sure how SEB would have fared in 2020s Hong Kong. Cursory research suggests that they may live on in Danang.\n\nWherever you might be, we wish you well, Shake ’em Buns. You saw us Millennials through our first tentative steps into dining out.\n\nIn the spirit of Openrice, we have this review for the restaurant’s Ghost Signs:\n\n“‘Tis GOOOOOOOD… the abandoned grand projecting sign is fab, still looms large over the corner of Wellington and Pottinger. The fonts are flavourful and brown with just the right amount of sans serif. Straight out of old-timey American kitsch. There’s just one last bite of juicy fascia sign left.”','\n',char(10)),0,'34 Pottinger St, Central District',1,'{"buildingName":"Pottinger Hse","buildingNumberFrom":"24","buildingNumberTo":"26","streetName":"Pottinger Street","neighbourhood":"Central District","district":null,"region":"HK","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('unvLyhWdWAb6','zh-hans','Skake Em Buns 汉堡店',0,replace('厨师对这个以汉堡为主题的 Ghost Sign 的亲吻。\n\n早在 2010 年代中期的汉堡热潮之前，香港就有 Shake ''em Buns——一家相当不错的美国主题汉堡店，是 2000 年代香港餐饮界的一部分。怀旧可能与此有关，但我们记得很享受它。\n\n一篇旧的 Openrice 评论是这样说的：\n“''这是 GOOOOOOOD....面包很棒，外面酥脆，里面柔软。肉味道鲜美，多汁，质地恰到好处，就像优质肉末一样。有恰到好处的脆皮生菜、西红柿和洋葱。\n\n这是一个喜欢一点影射的地方，其菜单项的名称并不像汉堡本身那样有品位——特色菜包括“Happy Threep”、“Debbie Does Dallas”和“Missionary”——所以我们不确定 SEB 在 2020 年代的香港会如何表现。粗略的研究表明，它们可能继续生活在岘港。\n\n无论您身在何处，我们都祝您一切顺利，Shake ''em Buns。您见证了我们千禧一代尝试外出就餐的第一步。\n\n本着 Openrice 的精神，我们对餐厅的 Ghost Signs 进行了以下评论：\n\n“''这是 GOOOOOOOD......废弃的宏伟突出标志 Fab 仍然在惠灵顿和砵甸乍的拐角处若隐若现。字体很有味道，呈棕色，带有适量的无衬线字体。直接来自老式的美国媚俗。只剩下最后一口多汁的筋膜标志了。','\n',char(10)),1,'宝城大厦砵典乍街24号中西区',1,'{"buildingName":"宝城大厦","buildingNumberFrom":"24","buildingNumberTo":"26","streetName":"砵典乍街","district":"中西区","region":null,"country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('unvLyhWdWAb6','zh-hant','Skake Em Buns漢堡店',0,replace('廚師對呢個以漢堡為主題嘅Ghost Sign嘅親吻。\n\n早喺2010年代中期嘅漢堡熱潮之前，香港就有Shake ''em Buns——一家相當唔錯嘅美國主題漢堡店，係2000年代香港餐飲界嘅一部分。 懷舊可能與此有關，但我哋記得好享受它。\n\n一篇舊嘅Openrice評論係咁講嘅：\n徜徉這是GOOOOOOOD.... 麵包好正，外面酥脆，裏面柔軟。 肉味道鮮甜，多汁，質地恰到好處，就好似優質肉末一樣。 有恰到好處嘅脆皮生菜、番茄同洋葱。\n\n這是一個喜歡一點影射的地方，其菜單項的名稱並不像漢堡本身那樣有品位——特色菜包括“Happy Threep”、“Debbie Does Dallas”和“Missionary”——所以我們不肯定SEB在2020年代的香港會如何表現。 粗略的研究表明，它們可能繼續生活喺峴港。\n\n無論您身在何處，我哋都祝你一切順利，Shake ''em Buns。 你見證咗我哋千禧一代嘗試外出就餐嘅第一步。\n\n本着Openrice嘅精神，我哋對餐廳嘅Ghost Signs進行了以下評論：\n\n徜徉這是GOOOOOOOD...... 廢棄嘅宏偉突出標誌Fab仍然喺惠靈頓同砵甸乍的枴角处若隱若現。 字體很有味道，呈棕色，帶有適量的無襯線字體。 直頭來自老式嘅美國媚俗。 只剩最後一口多汁嘅筋膜標誌了。','\n',char(10)),1,'寶城大廈砵典乍街24號中西區',1,'{"buildingName":"寶城大廈","buildingNumberFrom":"24","buildingNumberTo":"26","streetName":"砵典乍街","district":"中西區","region":null,"country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('S87lmZqsbSY-','en','Jumbo',0,replace('Everyone in Hong Kong knows the elaborate Ghost Signs on these deserted piers in Aberdeen. Silent since the pandemic, these once served the three floating restaurants, Tai Pak, Jumbo and Sea Palace, collectively known as “Jumbo Kingdom.”\n\nInspired by floating restaurants on fishermen’s barges and in typhoon shelters around Hong Kong and the Pearl River, Tai Pak was opened to great success in 1952. Hoping that lightning would strike twice, its owners began building Jumbo but ran into trouble in 1971 when fire broke out, killing 34 and injuring 42, before its opening. Jumbo eventually opened in 1976 backed by billionaire casino tycoon, Stanley Ho.\n\nFor decades, tourists flocked to Jumbo Kingdom, ferried to the imitation Ming Dynasty palaces aboard boats built in the same Shau Kei Wan shipyard that created the iconic Aqualuna junk. Serving Cantonese cuisine and seafood, Jumbo Kingdom played host to everyone from Chow Yun Fat to Queen Elizabeth and appeared in many movies including The Man With the Golden Gun, Infernal Affairs II, God of Cookery, and Noble House.\n\nThe Jumbo Kingdom has crumbled over the years. Sea Palace, whose name can still be seen in one Ghost Sign, was renamed ‘Jumbo Palace’ and sold off. In 1997, it was towed to Manila Bay but closed in 2008. It now lays derelict in Qingdao.\n\nJumbo became a casualty of the pandemic. With no tourists, the business fell into disrepair - the hull on its kitchen boat was breached and began to list. Many ambitious plans to preserve Jumbo were mooted, including making it a part of Ocean Park and transforming it into a Bruce Lee museum.\n\nWith losses rumoured to exceed HK$100 million, Jumbo was finally towed away in 2022 - its destination: Cambodia. The restaurant was never to be seen again. Just one day later Jumbo encountered bad weather and capsized near the Paracel Islands. Now resting 1,000m below the surface, Jumbo is little more than a legend and an eerie palace for the fishes.\n\nThere are plans afoot to resurrect the one floating restaurant that remains, Tai Pak, which was acquired in 2022. Its new owners had hoped to reopen for business in late 2024.','\n',char(10)),0,'3 Welfare Rd, Wong Chuk Hang',1,'{"buildingName":"Jumbo Court","buildingNumberFrom":"3","streetName":"Welfare Road","neighbourhood":"Wong Chuk Hang","district":"STH","region":"HK","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('S87lmZqsbSY-','zh-hans','巨型',1,replace('香港的每个人都知道香港仔这些荒凉码头上精心制作的幽灵标志。自大流行以来，这些餐厅一直保持沉寂，曾经为统称为“Jumbo Kingdom”的三家浮动餐厅 Tai Pak、Jumbo 和 Sea Palace 提供服务。\n\n受渔民驳船上以及香港和珠江周围避风塘中的浮动餐厅的启发，大白于 1952 年开业并取得巨大成功。希望闪电能击中两次，它的所有者开始建造 Jumbo，但在 1971 年发生火灾时遇到了麻烦，造成 34 人死亡，42 人受伤，然后才开业。Jumbo 最终于 1976 年开业，得到了亿万富翁赌场大亨 Stanley Ho 的支持。\n\n几十年来，游客涌向珍宝王国，乘坐造就标志性 Aqualuna 帆船的同一家筲箕湾造船厂建造的船只前往仿明朝宫殿。珍宝王国供应粤菜和海鲜，曾接待过从周润发到伊丽莎白女王的所有人，并出现在许多电影中，包括《金枪人》、《无间道 II》、《食神》和《贵屋》。\n\n多年来，珍宝王国已经崩溃。Sea Palace 的名字仍然可以在一个鬼标中看到，它被更名为“Jumbo Palace”并被出售。1997 年，它被拖到马尼拉湾，但于 2008 年关闭。它现在被遗弃在青岛。\n\nJumbo 成为大流行的牺牲品。由于没有游客，这家公司年久失修——其厨房船上的船体被破坏并开始倾斜。人们提出了许多雄心勃勃的计划来保护珍宝，包括将其作为海洋公园的一部分，并将其改造成李小龙博物馆。\n\n据传亏损超过 1 亿港元，Jumbo 终于在 2022 年被拖走——它的目的地：柬埔寨。这家餐厅再也没有出现过。仅仅一天后，Jumbo 遇到恶劣天气，在西沙群岛附近倾覆。现在，Jumbo 位于水面以下 1,000 米处，只不过是一个传说和鱼类的怪异宫殿。\n\n目前正计划恢复仅存的一家浮动餐厅 Tai Pak，该餐厅于 2022 年被收购。它的新所有者曾希望在 2024 年底重新开业。','\n',char(10)),1,'珍宝阁惠福道3号南区',1,'{"buildingName":"珍宝阁","buildingNumberFrom":"3","streetName":"惠福道","district":"南区","region":null,"country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('S87lmZqsbSY-','zh-hant','巨型',1,replace('香港嘅個個都知香港仔呢啲荒涼碼頭上精心製作嘅幽靈標誌。 自大流行以來，呢啲餐廳一直保持沉寂，曾經為統稱為“Jumbo Kingdom”嘅三家浮動餐廳Tai Pak、Jumbo同Sea Palace提供服務。\n\n受漁民駁船上以及香港同珠江周圍避風塘中嘅浮動餐廳嘅啟發，大白於1952年開業並取得巨大成功。 希望閃電擊中兩次得，它的所有者開始建造Jumbo，但喺1971年發生火災時遇到了麻煩，造成34人死亡，42人受傷，然後才開業。 Jumbo最終於1976年開業，得到咗億萬富翁賭場大亨Stanley Ho嘅撐。\n\n幾十年嚟，遊客湧向珍寶王國，乘坐造就標誌性Aqualuna帆船嘅同一家筲箕灣造船廠建造嘅船隻前往仿明朝宮殿。 珍寶王國供應粵菜和海鮮，曾接待過從周潤發到伊麗莎白女王的所有人，並出現在許多電影中，包括《金槍人》、《無間道II》、《食神》和《貴屋》。\n\n多年來，珍寶王國已經崩潰。 Sea Palace嘅名仍然可以喺一個鬼標中看到，它被更名為占Jumbo Palaceó並被出售。 1997年，它被拖到馬尼拉灣，但於2008年關閉。 它而家被遺棄喺青島。\n\nJumbo成為大流行嘅犧牲品。 由於冇遊客，呢間公司年久失修——其廚房船上嘅舩躰被破壞並開始傾斜。 人們提出咗好多雄心勃勃的計劃嚟保護珍寶，包括將其作為海洋公園嘅一部分，並將其改造成李小龍博物館。\n\n據傳虧損超過1億港元，Jumbo終於喺2022年被拖走——它的目的地：柬埔寨。 呢間餐廳再也沒有出現過。 僅僅一日之後，Jumbo遇到惡劣天氣，西沙羣島附近傾覆緊。 現時，Jumbo位於水面以下1,000米处，只不過係一個傳說同魚類嘅怪異宮殿。\n\n目前正計劃恢復僅存嘅一家浮動餐廳Tai Pak，該餐廳於2022年被收購。 它嘅新所有者曾希望在2024年底重新開業。','\n',char(10)),1,'珍寶閣惠福道3號南區',1,'{"buildingName":"珍寶閣","buildingNumberFrom":"3","streetName":"惠福道","district":"南區","region":null,"country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('8jMFSq-e94BH','en','Sung Wong Toi Rock Carving',0,'If there can be a Ghost Sign for an entire dynasty, then this rock outside Kowloon City is it.',0,'129 Ma Tau Chung Rd, Kowloon City',1,'{"buildingName":"Wai Tak House","buildingNumberFrom":"129","streetName":"Ma Tau Chung Road","neighbourhood":"Kowloon City","district":"KLC","region":"KL","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('8jMFSq-e94BH','zh-hans','新黄台石刻',1,'如果整个朝代都可以有一个鬼星座，那么九龙城外的这块石头就是它。',1,'伟德楼马头涌道129号九龙城区',1,'{"buildingName":"伟德楼","buildingNumberFrom":"129","streetName":"马头涌道","neighbourhood":"九龙城","district":"九龙城区","region":"九龙","country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('8jMFSq-e94BH','zh-hant','新黃台石刻',1,'如果成個朝代都可以有一個鬼星座，咁九龍城外嘅嚿石就係它。',1,'偉德樓馬頭涌道129號九龍城區',1,'{"buildingName":"偉德樓","buildingNumberFrom":"129","streetName":"馬頭涌道","neighbourhood":"九龍城","district":"九龍城區","region":"九龍","country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('Bjo2exvsFC8y','en','發 Revealed By Car Accident',0,replace('When a car crashed into the side of this building at 60 Hollywood Road, it cracked off a large stone slab - one that had a Ghost Sign carved into it! It read "廣成建築裝公司設計 電話 二四三七五" (Designed by Kwong Shing Architectural Decoration Company Phone: 24375).\n\nThe car left a hole in the wall, revealing an old terrazzo sign that is seeing light for the first time in decades. One red character still reads as clearly as it would have done in its heyday,"發" (faat3).\n\nAccording to many sources, the shophouse at No. 60 was built in the mid 1920s but records from Wah Yan College state that Mr. Peter Tsui Yan Sau founded their school with four students at this site in 1919. In 1921 Wah Yan moved to 2 Robinson Road.\n\nDuring its stint at No. 60, Wah Yan occupied the 3rd and 4th floors so it’s unlikely that the Ghost Sign belonged to them. However, the ground floor tenant was Sui Man Book Store, which sold cultural books and banned publications associated with the New Culture Movement.\n\nBorn of disillusionment with the Republic of China during the 1910s and 1920s, the New Culture Movement opposed traditional Confucian values and advocated a new Chinese Culture favouring progressive democratic ideals, women’s liberation, individual freedom, and science.\n\nThe New Culture Movement was associated with literature written in vernacular Chinese. “Speak in the language of the time in which you live,” said Hu Shih, whose writings were likely sold at Sui Man along with banned texts by contemporaries like Lu Xun.\n\nSui Man Book Store would have been one of the few, if not the only place, to get your copy of “Diary of a Madman” and police reportedly patrolled the block. Customers looking to buy illicit titles would have to ask the shopkeeper specifically, perhaps even giving a code word. The goods would then be produced from a hidden compartment.\n\nSui Man Book Store closed after WWII and the herbal tea shop opened up shortly thereafter, perhaps hiding this sign for decades...','\n',char(10)),0,'60 Hollywood Rd, Central District',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"60","streetName":"Hollywood Road","neighbourhood":"Central District","district":null,"region":"HK","country":"HKSAR"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('Bjo2exvsFC8y','zh-hans','發 车祸揭露',1,replace('当一辆汽车撞上这座位于荷李活道 60 号的建筑的一侧时，它从一块大石板上裂开——一块上面刻有鬼标志的石板！上面写着“廣成建华公司設計 二四三七五”（由广盛建筑装饰公司设计 电话：24375）。\n\n汽车在墙上留下了一个洞，露出了一个几十年来第一次看到光明的旧水磨石标志。一个红色字符的读起来仍然像鼎盛时期一样清晰，“發”（faat3）。\n\n根据许多消息来源，位于 60 号的店屋建于 1920 年代中期，但华仁书院的记录表明，Peter Tsui Yan Sau 先生于 1919 年与四名学生在此地创立了他们的学校。1921 年，华仁搬到罗便臣道 2 号。\n\n在 60 号任职期间，华仁占据了 3 楼和 4 楼，因此鬼标不太可能属于他们。然而，底层的租户是遂民书店，该书店出售文化书籍和与新文化运动相关的禁书。\n\n新文化运动诞生于 1910 年代和 1920 年代对中华民国的幻灭，反对传统的儒家价值观，倡导有利于进步民主理想、妇女解放、个人自由和科学的新中国文化。\n\n新文化运动与用中国白话写成的文学有关。“用你生活的时代的语言说话，”胡 Shih说，他的著作很可能与鲁迅等同时代人的禁书一起在隋赣出售。\n\n隋民书店（Sui Man Book Store）是少数几个可以买到《狂人日记》（Diary of a Madman）的地方之一，据报道，警察在街区巡逻。想要购买非法书刊的顾客必须专门询问店主，甚至可能给出一个暗号。然后，货物将从隐藏的隔间中生产出来。\n\n二战后，隋民书店关门了，凉茶店不久后就开了，也许这个标志隐藏了几十年......','\n',char(10)),1,'荷李活道60号中西区',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"60","streetName":"荷李活道","district":"中西区","region":null,"country":"香港特区"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('Bjo2exvsFC8y','zh-hant','發現車揭露',1,replace('当一輛汽車撞上這座位於荷李活道60號嘅建築嘅一側時，它由一塊大石板上裂開——一塊上面刻有鬼標誌嘅石板！ 上面寫著“廣成建華公司設計二四三七五”（由廣盛建築裝飾公司設計電話：24375）。\n\n汽車喺牆上留低咗一個洞，露出了一個幾十年嚟第一次睇到光明嘅舊水磨石標誌。 一個紅色字符嘅讀起來仍然像鼎盛時期一樣清晰，“發”（ faat3 ）。\n\n根據好多消息來源，位於60號嘅店屋建於1920年代中期，但華仁書院嘅記錄表明，Peter Tsui Yan Sau先生於1919年與四名學生在此地創立咗佢哋嘅學校。 1921年，華仁搬到罗便臣道2號。\n\n在60號任職期間，華仁佔據了3樓同4樓，因此鬼標唔太可能屬於佢哋。 然而，底層嘅租戶係遂民書店，該書店出售文化書籍同與新文化運動相關嘅禁書。\n\n新文化運動誕生於1910年代同1920年代對中華民國嘅幻滅，反對傳統嘅儒家價值觀，倡導益咗進步民主理想、婦女解放、個人自由同科學新中國文化。\n\n新文化運動與用中國白話寫成嘅文學有關。 “用你生活嘅時代嘅語言講話，”胡Shih話，佢嘅著作好可能與魯迅等同時代人嘅禁書一齊喺隋贛出售。\n\n隋民書店（ Sui Man Book Store ）係少數幾個可以買到《狂人日記》（Diary of a Madman ）嘅地方之一，據報道，警察在街區巡邏。 想要購買非法書刊嘅顧客必須專門詢問店主，甚至可能畀出一個暗號。 然後，貨物將由隱藏嘅隔間中生產出嚟。\n\n二戰後，隋民書店關門了，涼茶店不久後就開了，也許這個標誌隱藏了幾十年......','\n',char(10)),1,'荷李活道60號中西區',1,'{"buildingNumberFrom":"60","streetName":"荷李活道","district":"中西區","region":null,"country":"香港特區"}');
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('IGo2AHNbLrtU','en','Oxford St., Shing Mun Redoubt',0,replace('Built on the beautiful northern slopes of Smuggler’s Ridge with a commanding view over Tsuen Wan and Shing Mun Reservoir, facilities include an observation post, four pillboxes, and a network of subterranean tunnels. \012\012Also known as <b>Shing Mun Redoubt</b>, the labyrinth of tunnels was named for the glitzy streets of London by the Middlesex Regiment who were stationed here in WWII. They kept up a healthy dose of gallows humour as they patrolled “Charing Cross,” “Shaftesbury Avenue,” “Regent Street,” “Haymarket,” and “Piccadilly Circus.""\012\012We explored the Ghost Signs of these tunnels with Dr. Kwong Chi Man of @hk1941spatialhistory an expert on the Battle of Hong Kong.\n\nShing Mun Redoubt was part of an 18km British Military defensive line, known as “The Gin Drinkers Line.” The line was constructed between 1936 and 1938 to protect Kowloon in anticipation of a Japanese invasion from the North. The Strand Palace Hotel acted as a headquarters and observation post which could contact Mount Davis Battery and Stonecutters Island Fort by telephone in order to aid those positions in aiming their large guns.\012\012Garrisoned by only 42 men, the Japanese found no difficulty in capturing the position on 9/12/1941. Thinking it would be difficult, they deployed 800 men to crack the Redoubt, easily taking it with many wounded, three dead and one M.I.A. on the British side.\012\012The Ghost Signs themselves are neatly moulded into the concrete walls of the redoubt. Rendered in a clean sans serif typeface they are still very legible. Their utilitarian design would have been ideal for their purpose - quickly directing soldiers around the fortification.\012\012We’re still researching the exact font which was used and some sources claim it was just a standard lettering kit issued across the British Empire for military use. Dr. Kwong suspects a relationship between the font used at the Redoubt and that used on British motorways at the time - Ministry. There are some differences though and Dr. Kwong guesses that this could have happened as a result of the local Hong Kong craftsmen who were engaged to create the metal lettering moulds.",114.146026,22.375492,"94GW+5C Kwai Chung, Hong Kong','\012',char(10)),0,'94GW+QW, Lo Wai, Kwai Chung',0,NULL);
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('IGo2AHNbLrtU','zh-hans','牛津街、城门堡垒',1,replace('该博物馆建在美丽的走私者岭北坡，可俯瞰荃湾和城门水塘，设施包括一个观察站、四个碉堡和一个地下隧道网络。迷宫般的隧道也被称为城门堡垒，由二战期间驻扎在这里的米德尔塞克斯军团以伦敦耀眼的街道命名。他们在巡逻“查令十字街”、“沙夫茨伯里大道”、“摄政街”、“干草市场”和“皮卡迪利广场”时保持了适度的刑架幽默。\n\n我们与香港战役专家@hk1941spatialhistory Kwong Chi Man 博士一起探索了这些隧道的幽灵迹象。城门堡垒是英国军队一条 18 公里防线的一部分，被称为“杜松子酒者防线”。该线路建于 1936 年至 1938 年之间，旨在保护九龙，以应对日本从北方入侵。斯特兰德宫酒店充当总部和观察站，可以通过电话联系戴维斯山炮台和昂船洲堡垒，以帮助这些阵地瞄准他们的大型火炮。\n\n日本人只有 42 人驻守，在 1941 年 9 月 12 日占领该阵地没有遇到任何困难。他们认为这会很困难，于是部署了 800 人来破解堡垒，轻松占领了堡垒，英方伤员多，三人死亡，一名 MIA。\n\n鬼标志本身被整齐地塑造在堡垒的混凝土墙上。以干净的无衬线字体呈现，它们仍然非常清晰。他们的实用设计本来非常适合他们的目的——快速引导士兵绕过防御工事。\n\n我们仍在研究所使用的确切字体，一些消息来源声称它只是大英帝国为军事用途而发行的标准刻字套件。邝博士怀疑堡垒使用的字体与当时英国高速公路上使用的字体 Ministry 之间存在关系。虽然存在一些差异，但邝博士猜测这可能是由于香港当地的工匠参与了金属刻字模具的制作。“，114.146026,22.375492，”94GW+5C Kwai Chung， Hong Kong','\n',char(10)),0,'葵涌老围94GW+QW',0,NULL);
INSERT INTO featureI18n VALUES('IGo2AHNbLrtU','zh-hant','牛津街、城門堡壘',1,replace('該博物館建喺靚嘅走私者嶺北坡，可俯瞰荃灣同城門水塘，設施包括一個觀察企、四個碉堡同一個地下隧道網絡。 迷宮般嘅隧道都被稱為城門堡壘，由二戰期間駐紮喺呢度嘅米德尔塞克斯軍團以倫敦耀眼嘅街道命名。 他們在巡邏“查令十字街”、“沙夫茨伯里大道”、“攝政街”、“乾草市場”和“皮卡迪利廣場”時保持了適度的刑架幽默。\n\n我哋與香港戰役專家@hk1941spatialhistory Kwong Chi Man博士一起探索咗呢啲隧道嘅幽靈迹象。城門堡壘係英國軍隊一條18公里防線嘅一部分，被稱為“杜松子酒者防線”。 該線路建於1936年至1938年之間，旨在保護九龍，以應對日本由北方入侵。 斯特兰德宫酒店充當總部同觀察企，可以透過電話聯繫戴維斯山炮台同昂船洲堡壘，以幫助呢啲陣地瞄準他們的大型火炮。\n\n日本人只有42人駐守，在1941年9月12日佔領該陣地冇遇到任何困難。 佢哋認為會好困難，于是部署了800人嚟破解堡壘，輕鬆佔領咗堡壘，英方傷員多，三人死亡，一名MIA。\n\n鬼標誌本身被整齊地塑造喺堡壘嘅混凝土牆上。 以乾淨嘅無襯綫字體呈現，它們仍然非常清晰。 佢哋嘅實用設計本來非常適合他們的目的——快速引導士兵繞過防禦工事。\n\n我哋仍在研究所使用的確切字體，一些消息來源聲稱它只是大英帝国嘅為軍事用途而發行嘅標準刻字套件。 鄺博士懷疑堡壘使用嘅字體與當時英國高速公路上使用嘅字體Ministry之間存在關係。 雖然存在一些差異，但鄺博士猜測可能係由於香港當地嘅工匠參與咗金屬刻字模具嘅製作。“，114.146026,22.375492，”94GW+5C Kwai Chung，Hong Kong','\n',char(10)),0,'葵湧老圍94GW+QW',0,NULL);
